{"type":"message","id":"3c0e4b29","parentId":"67a1998e","timestamp":"2026-05-23T01:40:51.226Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the issue. Looking at the config, the `allowFrom` for feishu is:\n```json\n\"allowFrom\": [\n  \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n],\n\"groupAllowFrom\": [\n  \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n]\n```\n\nThis is at the top level (feishu.defaultAccount is \"kiit\"). But the tts account doesn't have its own `allowFrom` defined, so it inherits... wait, actually each account has its own config.\n\nLooking at the tts account:\n```json\n\"tts\": {\n  \"appId\": \"cli_a930f78f51399bc6\",\n  \"appSecret\": \"***\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"name\": \"TK 选品大师\"\n}\n```\n\nIt doesn't have `allowFrom` specified, so it uses the default from the parent level.\n\nBut wait - the messages search from yesterday shows that a fix was already applied at 16:08:24:\n```\n\"TK 选品大师的账号 allowFrom 白名单只授权了另一个用户，**没有包含你的 open_id**（`ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb`），所以它的飞书账号收不到你的消息。\n\n已修复 ✅ 重新配置了白名单。\n```\n\nSo the tts `allowFrom` was fixed. Let me check if that fix is still in effect or if something reverted it.\n\nLooking at the current config, tts account doesn't have its own `allowFrom`. The parent level has `allowFrom: [\"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"]`. Since `tts` inherits from the parent level by default, this should work.\n \nThe system message at 16:08 shows the tts allowFrom was patched to include the user's open_id, but the current config doesn't show a separate allowFrom on the tts account itself—it would need to be explicitly set to override the parent. The issue might be that when hot-reload happened, the patch didn't persist properly in the JSON hierarchy.\n\nLooking at the Gateway status from May 23, there's a critical error: `Gateway: channels.feishu.accounts.tts failed`. The account failed to load, which means the tts configuration may have been corrupted or the account is completely non-functional now.\n\nI need to determine if the tts account is actually operational or if it's completely broken. Let me check the account status to understand the current state.\n","thinkingSignature":"55a4a2e436b77dcd669d6be60d8b26506e2b66fd0b43e12074a7e25923e5562d"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找到了！昨天的问题和解决方案已经很清楚了。让我确认一下当前状态：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p6vgr0li0bf9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/halei/.openclaw && openclaw status 2>&1 | head -60"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6525,"output":608,"cacheRead":60854,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67987,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779500434256,"responseId":"066038926ca78204840443aa65467d7a"}}
