{"type":"message","id":"4859b7a6","parentId":"3cd7f6c4","timestamp":"2026-05-23T01:41:38.482Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the problem now. The tts account configuration is missing several key fields that were likely configured in yesterday's fix:\n\nLooking at the config:\n- `appId`: cli_a930f78f51399bc6 ✓\n- `appSecret`: set ✓\n- `enabled`: true ✓\n- `name`: \"TK 选品大师\" ✓\n\nBut it's missing:\n- `allowFrom` - which yesterday's log said was added to fix the issue (白名单授权)\n\nWait, looking back at the search results, the issue yesterday was:\n> \"TK 选品大师的账号 allowFrom 白名单只授权了另一个用户，**没有包含你的 open_id**（`ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb`），所以它的飞书账号收不到你的消息。已修复 ✅ 重新配置了白名单。\"\n\n\nThe timestamp shows this was fixed on May 22 at 16:08, but the config I'm looking at now only has the basic fields. Either the hot-reload didn't persist the allowFrom changes, or I'm looking at a stale version of the config that doesn't reflect what was actually applied.\n\nThe user is reporting the same problem persists, so I should verify the current state of the tts account configuration to see if the fix actually took.\n","thinkingSignature":"77b534f47c1a947230fbf1dbbc672009b037c355cbdb9403a8b9bf95406ed4c8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_au9hp8hd8164_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A20 '\"allowFrom\"' /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json | head -80","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":168,"output":330,"cacheRead":67817,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68315,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779500492042,"responseId":"066038cc37f6904791c90f1401d55129"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5f6949c1","parentId":"4859b7a6","timestamp":"2026-05-23T01:41:38.732Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_au9hp8hd8164_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"allowFrom\": [\n        \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n      ],\n      \"groupAllowFrom\": [\n        \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"wecom\": {\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"botId\": \"aib4H1edblYf-DEub6oxTN2s-B4WLkE5PDc\",\n      \"secret\": \"JfFd6m…AUhi\"\n    },\n    \"openclaw-weixin\": {\n      \"channelConfigUpdatedAt\": \"2026-05-22T12:51:35.188Z\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"lastTouchedVersion\": \"2026.5.20\",\n    \"lastTouchedAt\": \"2026-05-22T14:29:46.131Z\"\n  },\n  \"gateway\": {"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":44,"aggregated":"\"allowFrom\": [\n        \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n      ],\n      \"groupAllowFrom\": [\n        \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"wecom\": {\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"botId\": \"aib4H1edblYf-DEub6oxTN2s-B4WLkE5PDc\",\n      \"secret\": \"***\"\n    },\n    \"openclaw-weixin\": {\n      \"channelConfigUpdatedAt\": \"2026-05-22T12:51:35.188Z\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"lastTouchedVersion\": \"2026.5.20\",\n    \"lastTouchedAt\": \"2026-05-22T14:29:46.131Z\"\n  },\n  \"gateway\": {","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779500498728}}
{"type":"message","id":"a5270b57","parentId":"5f6949c1","timestamp":"2026-05-23T01:41:57.990Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the `allowFrom` and `groupAllowFrom` are only under the `default` account, not under the `tts` account. And the `dmPolicy` is \"allowlist\" at the top level.\n\nThe issue is that when a user sends a DM to the tts bot, if the tts account has `dmPolicy: allowlist` and `allowFrom` isn't set for tts, then only explicitly whitelisted users can DM it.\n\nThe user's open_id `ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb` is in the global `allowFrom` list at the feishu channel level, but the tts account needs its own `allowFrom` entry to allow this user.\n\nActually, let me re-check. Looking at the previous message history from the search, on May 22 they already fixed the allowFrom issue once:\n\n```\n\"message_id\": \"om_x100b6e34a1b6b960b4cb0da7be6e6e1\",\n\"content\": \"TK 选品大师的账号 allowFrom 白名单只授权了另一个用户，**没有包含你的 open_id**（`ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb`），所以它的飞书账号收不到你的消息。\\n\\n已修复 ✅ 重新配置了白名单。\n\n建议等 1 分钟让配置生效，然后再给 TK 选品大师 发消息试试。如果还有问题我们再排查。\n```\n\nSo they already fixed this. But then there was still a problem afterward. Let me check what the \"still not working\" situation was from the May 22 conversation.\n\nAfter the allowFrom fix, there was still an issue. The logs show the user was saying the tts bot is not responding even after the allowFrom was fixed. That's when they escalated to checking the webhook/app_id etc.\n\nThe last message in the search shows the assistant was asking the user to confirm the TK bot's app_id in Feishu.\n\nSo it seems like on May 22, after the allowFrom fix was applied, there was still no response from tts. The last message from the conversation was around 21:07 on May 22, where the assistant was asking the user to verify the app_id.\n\nThe user says \"不记得昨天说的了吗\" - so what's the status now? Maybe the user is asking me to check what was the last state, and we need to verify if the fix worked or if there's still an issue.\n\nLet me check the current tts account configuration and see if there's an issue with the allowFrom that might have regressed or something.\n","thinkingSignature":"b17808f227f5330455d2f1f8649524674a9349199394e76c638c37b4af3e4c0a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8wx864sg5hhp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\ntts = cfg['channels']['feishu']['accounts']['tts']\nprint('allowFrom:', tts.get('allowFrom', 'NOT SET'))\nprint('dmPolicy:', tts.get('dmPolicy', 'NOT SET'))\nprint('enabled:', tts.get('enabled'))\nprint('appId:', tts.get('appId'))\nprint()\n# Check if global allowFrom is inherited\ndefault = cfg['channels']['feishu']['accounts'].get('default', {})\nprint('default allowFrom:', default.get('allowFrom', 'NOT SET'))\nprint('default dmPolicy:', default.get('dmPolicy', 'NOT SET'))\nprint()\n# Check top-level allowFrom\ntop = cfg['channels']['feishu']\nprint('top-level allowFrom:', top.get('allowFrom', 'NOT SET'))\nprint('top-level dmPolicy:', top.get('dmPolicy', 'NOT SET'))\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":278,"output":804,"cacheRead":67982,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69064,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779500498840,"responseId":"066038d3657f26a93386c1cde9285597"}}
