{"type":"message","id":"872b8d4f","parentId":"426a27e3","timestamp":"2026-05-23T01:42:39.981Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lstysg817x6b_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"description\": \"选品专家 Agent - 负责产品筛选、市场调研、竞品分析、选品策略制定\",\n  \"capabilities\": [\n    \"市场潜力评估\",\n    \"竞品分析\",\n    \"产品筛选\",\n    \"数据驱动选品\"\n  ],\n  \"model\": \"gemini/gemini-2.0-flash\",\n  \"workspaceDir\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/Selector\",\n  \"tools\": {\n    \"allow\": [\n      \"cron\",\n      \"read\",\n      \"write\",\n      \"edit\",\n      \"apply_patch\",\n      \"memory_search\",\n      \"memory_get\",\n      \"browser\",\n      \"message\",\n      \"exec\",\n      \"web_search\",\n      \"web_fetch\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-27T19:45:00+08:00\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":70,"aggregated":"{\n  \"description\": \"选品专家 Agent - 负责产品筛选、市场调研、竞品分析、选品策略制定\",\n  \"capabilities\": [\n    \"市场潜力评估\",\n    \"竞品分析\",\n    \"产品筛选\",\n    \"数据驱动选品\"\n  ],\n  \"model\": \"gemini/gemini-2.0-flash\",\n  \"workspaceDir\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/Selector\",\n  \"tools\": {\n    \"allow\": [\n      \"cron\",\n      \"read\",\n      \"write\",\n      \"edit\",\n      \"apply_patch\",\n      \"memory_search\",\n      \"memory_get\",\n      \"browser\",\n      \"message\",\n      \"exec\",\n      \"web_search\",\n      \"web_fetch\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-27T19:45:00+08:00\"\n}","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779500559979}}
{"type":"message","id":"6858067c","parentId":"872b8d4f","timestamp":"2026-05-23T01:42:51.134Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the tts agent config - but wait, the current OpenClaw config shows tts agent uses `minimax/MiniMax-M2.7`, not `gemini/gemini-2.0-flash`. That config file might be stale. The current config already has tts agent using `minimax/MiniMax-M2.7`.\n\nNow I need to understand the actual problem. Let me think about what I know:\n\n1. Yesterday's conversation showed the user was trying to message TK 选品大师 via Feishu but getting no response\n2. The messages were being routed to `Feishu[default]` (kiit) instead of `Feishu[tts]`\n3. The analysis pointed to the `allowFrom` whitelist not including the user for the tts account\n\nBut the tts account doesn't have its own `allowFrom` set, so it inherits... actually wait - does it inherit from the top-level or from the default? Let me check what happens when an account doesn't specify allowFrom.\n\nIn the current config, tts has NO allowFrom set, no dmPolicy set. The top-level feishu has allowFrom with the user's open_id and dmPolicy=allowlist.\n\nIf tts inherits from top-level, then the user's open_id IS in the allowFrom. So that shouldn't be the problem.\n\nWait, let me re-examine the routing. If the user is sending messages to the TK bot via Feishu, but they're going to Feishu[default] instead of Feishu[tts], that means the message routing isn't working correctly.\n\nThere could be several reasons:\n1. The tts bot's webhook isn't set up correctly in Feishu\n2. The tts bot app is not properly configured in Feishu to receive messages\n3. The connection mode is wrong\n\nLet me check if there's a way to verify if the tts account is actually connected and receiving messages. Let me look at the workspace-tts directory to see if there's any state.\n\n\nThe most likely culprit is that the tts bot's webhook in Feishu isn't pointing to the right endpoint or isn't configured at all. Since the user is using websocket mode (connectionMode: websocket in the config), the webhook path shouldn't matter for receiving messages - but if Feishu is treating the tts bot differently than expected, the messages could still be getting routed to the default account instead.\n\nLooking at the search results from yesterday, the tts account was modified and the user was told to wait for configuration to take effect. But this morning the user is reporting that the problem persists. I need to check the current tts account status in the config to see if the allowFrom is properly set, since that was the originally identified issue. Let me look at the full tts account configuration to understand what's currently wrong.\n","thinkingSignature":"a9b81f1c3fb0f0967e7cd58a25758209923ec15054de71a315c111f1d824abe6"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n根据昨天对话的记录，问题是 **TK 选品大师的 allowFrom 白名单没有包含你的 open_id**，当时做了修复。但现在你又反映有问题，可能是配置在重启后没有完全生效，或者有新的问题。\n\n让我检查一下当前 tts 的完整配置：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_eqrlcxkbcg4b_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\ntts = cfg['channels']['feishu']['accounts']['tts']\nfor k,v in tts.items():\n    print(f'{k}: {v}')\nprint()\ndefault = cfg['channels']['feishu']['accounts'].get('default', {})\nprint('--- default account ---')\nfor k,v in default.items():\n    print(f'{k}: {v}')\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":812,"output":783,"cacheRead":70823,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72418,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779500560119,"responseId":"066039106d02125bd5c2cddaf1a96378"}}
