{"type":"message","id":"def87725","parentId":"e7eccfff","timestamp":"2026-05-23T01:43:18.476Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see what's happening. The tts agent IS running - it has a session from today (May 23) at 09:00 that ran a cron job for daily product selection. But the last message shows an error: \"server is busy, please retry later\" - this is from MiniMax API being overloaded.\n\nBut more importantly - when the user sends a DM to the TK 选品大师 bot in Feishu, the messages are all going to `Feishu[default]` (kiit) instead of `Feishu[tts]`. Let me look at the router config to understand why.\n\nLet me check what happens when a message comes in - it should be routed based on `accountId`. The tts account has `appId: cli_a930f78f51399bc6`. When a user sends a DM to that bot, Feishu delivers it to that app. The gateway should route it to the `tts` account based on the appId.\n\nWait - but the user's messages ARE going to kiit (default account). That means when the user opens the TK bot conversation in Feishu and sends a message, Feishu is delivering it to `cli_a93650c6fc785bce` (kiit app) instead of `cli_a930f78f51399bc6` (tts app).\n\nThis could mean either:\n1. The user is actually DMing the kiit bot, not the tts bot\n2. There's some routing issue in the Feishu app configuration\n\nLet me check the router config to understand the routing logic.\n","thinkingSignature":"d99ea6fdc1b58cb802a69ec7477b7b57dafb2ccfb513ff8a4ccb4654251ea273"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2d9jmf7noapv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A30 '\"router\"' /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json | head -60","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6255,"output":388,"cacheRead":72125,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78768,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779500587525,"responseId":"0660392ccac5c7164c1f