{"type":"message","id":"381693fd","parentId":"c09bed92","timestamp":"2026-05-23T11:55:18.340Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No routes configured at all! That's the problem. Routes are how OpenClaw routes incoming messages to the correct agent/account. Since there are no routes, when a user sends a message to TK 选品大师's bot (appId cli_a930f78f51399bc6), OpenClaw doesn't know how to route it to the tts agent.\n\nThe routes should include something that maps incoming messages for the tts account to the tts agent. Let me check what routes we need.\n\nLooking at the agent config for tts:\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"tts\",\n  \"match\": {\n    \"accountId\": \"tts\",\n    \"channel\": \"feishu\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSo there should be a route that maps feishu account=tts to agentId=tts. Without this route, even though the tts account is configured and has the correct allowFrom/dmPolicy, OpenClaw doesn't know how to route the incoming message.\n\nLet me check if there's a routes configuration in the file that I missed.\n","thinkingSignature":"5e695b27f004027989014b0a3213af196303148cba0ff61f28f7ae8114f204ca"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n68258p27t2w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"routes\" /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json | head -5","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":166,"output":274,"cacheRead":87846,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88286,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779537306776,"responseId":"0660c8a0b537321b4fb08cc1f2609a45"}}
