{"type":"message","id":"069c4686","parentId":"e2b0f48f","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:06:45.314Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the OpenClaw gateway is running (pid 499639). It's connected to various IPs including some that could be Feishu servers (36.155.182.76, 111.63.180.182, 111.31.21.135, etc.) via HTTPS on port 443. This confirms the WebSocket connections to Feishu are active.\n\nNow, the WebUI shows the TK bot status correctly. The bot has `dmPolicy: allowlist` and `allowFrom: ou_f590c429...`. The connectionMode is `websocket`. So the config looks correct from what we can see in the UI.\n \nThe issue is that when the user sends a message directly to the TK bot in Feishu, it goes to the `cli_a930f78f51399bc6` app. Since both accounts use the same gateway, the message should be received via the established WebSocket connection and routed to the tts agent. But since the user reports it doesn't work, something's preventing the message from reaching the agent or the response from coming back. Let me check the gateway logs to see what's actually happening.\n","thinkingSignature":"6a9e43a234f14b0012149bfaa2d6de9d15e73edfefe805cfe579cc906dc6ddec"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1pqou2ki9fbd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -n 200 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"tts\\|cli_a930\\|account\\|route\\|feishu.*incoming\\|incoming.*feishu\" | tail -30","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1243,"output":320,"cacheRead":91827,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93390,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779537994644,"responseId":"0660cb4b6f2078c3283dc5d6a83ddf5d"}}
