{"type":"message","id":"346aa499","parentId":"62c0d3e6","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:08:16.247Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see it! There are 3 sessions for tts:1. `agent:tts:main` - updatedAt=1779537871917 (recent, this is the web UI session!)\n2. `agent:tts:cron:...` - updatedAt=1779498002300 (the 9AM cron run)\n3. `agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` - updatedAt=1777380099043 (old session for another user)\n\nThere's NO session for `agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb`! The user's open_id is `ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb`, but there's no feishu direct session with that open_id.\nThe `agent:tts:main` session exists and is active (updated just now at 1779537871917), which corresponds to the web UI session.\n\nSo the issue is clear now: when the user sends a message via the TK bot in Feishu (app_id `cli_a930f78f51399bc6`), OpenClaw should route it to the tts agent. \n\nBut there are two possibilities: either the route isn't set up correctly, or the tts agent is routing to the wrong channel. Looking at the session keys, the kiit agent has a session like `agent:main:feishu:default:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb`, but the tts agent's feishu session is mapped to `ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` instead. Since the user doesn't appear in the tts session mapping, their message to the TK bot likely isn't being routed to the tts agent at all—it's probably going to kiit instead.\n\nActually, wait. The `agent:tts:main` session exists (that's the web UI session), so the routing should theoretically work. But the user is saying it doesn't work via Feishu, only via web UI. So maybe there's a session naming issue where the tts agent's main session is being used for feishu direct messages when it shouldn't be, or maybe the session key for feishu is being constructed incorrectly and is missing the user ID entirely.\n\nLet me check if OpenClaw supports routing rules that might help clarify this, since the config doesn't show any explicit routes.\n\nActually, I should think about this from the Feishu webhook perspective: when a message arrives at the TK bot, Feishu sends it to the webhook with the app_id in the payload. OpenClaw uses this app_id to match against account configs and route to the right agent. The app_id `cli_a930f78f51399bc6` is configured for the tts account, so the routing logic should work. But maybe the issue is that after the gateway restart, the tts agent's websocket connection to Feishu isn't properly established, or there's a mismatch in how the agentId is being resolved from the account configuration.\n\nLet me check the OpenClaw status to see the actual channel connections and verify which accounts are actively connected.\n","thinkingSignature":"2683fa19b532fdfbe89687223aed34b574106819c9ff718b79a9e3a47cfa6359"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9034vdnhfv1t_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/sessions/sessions.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\n# Show all sessions with full info\nfor k, v in data.items():\n    print(f'Key: {k}')\n    print(f'  updatedAt: {v.get(\\\"updatedAt\\\")}')\n    print(f'  lastMessage: {str(v.get(\\\"lastMessage\\\", \\\"\\\"))[:200]}')\n    print(f'  channel: {v.get(\\\"channel\\\")}')\n    print(f'  origin: {v.get(\\\"origin\\\")}')\n    print()\n\" 2>/dev/null","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":412,"output":883,"cacheRead":93385,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94680,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779538072442,"responseId":"0660cb9aa64c9bec7806053e28e0ae7a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e1e0c5b7","parentId":"346aa499","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:08:16.657Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9034vdnhfv1t_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key: agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\n  updatedAt: 1777380099043\n  lastMessage: \n  channel: None\n  origin: {'label': 'ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68', 'provider': 'feishu', 'surface': 'feishu', 'chatType': 'direct', 'from': 'feishu:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68', 'to': 'user:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68', 'accountId': 'tts'}\n\nKey: agent:tts:main\n  updatedAt: 1779537871917\n  lastMessage: \n  channel: None\n  origin: {'provider': 'webchat', 'surface': 'webchat', 'chatType': 'direct'}\n\nKey: agent:tts:cron:5c75bbb4-b1c3-446b-bde9-74bed5a396c6\n  updatedAt: 1779498002300\n  lastMessage: \n  channel: None\n  origin: None"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":81,"aggregated":"Key: agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\n  updatedAt: 1777380099043\n  lastMessage: \n  channel: None\n  origin: {'label': 'ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68', 'provider': 'feishu', 'surface': 'feishu', 'chatType': 'direct', 'from': 'feishu:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68', 'to': 'user:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68', 'accountId': 'tts'}\n\nKey: agent:tts:main\n  updatedAt: 1779537871917\n  lastMessage: \n  channel: None\n  origin: {'provider': 'webchat', 'surface': 'webchat', 'chatType': 'direct'}\n\nKey: agent:tts:cron:5c75bbb4-b1c3-446b-bde9-74bed5a396c6\n  updatedAt: 1779498002300\n  lastMessage: \n  channel: None\n  origin: None","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779538096655}}
{"type":"message","id":"c3c46d7d","parentId":"e1e0c5b7","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:08:57.718Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture:\n\n1. **agent:tts:main** - updatedAt=1779537871917 (that's in about 15 seconds from now, very recent) - this is the web UI session! It's currently active.\n2. **agent:tts:cron:5c75bbb4-b1c3-446b-bde9-74bed5a396c6** - updatedAt=1779498002300 (today 09:00) - cron job triggered session\n3. **agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68** - updatedAt=1777380099043 (old session, May 16 or so)\n\nSo `agent:tts:main` is a webchat session, not a Feishu session. And it's VERY recent (updated in the last ~15 seconds). That's the web UI session that the user is using to test TK.\n\nBut there's NO session for `agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb`!\n\nThe user's open_id is `ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb`, but the tts session that exists for feishu is:\n- `agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` - which is a DIFFERENT user (ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68)\n\nSo when the user (ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb) sends a message to the TK bot, what happens?\n\n\nThe Feishu message comes in with the TK bot's app_id (cli_a930f78f51399bc6) and user sender (ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb), and the system needs to route this to the tts agent with the feishu channel and account. Since there's no existing session for this user-account combination, a new session would be created. But there IS a session at `agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` for a different user, which suggests the routing might be misconfigured or the new user session isn't being properly established.\n\nThe issue could be that when Feishu sends a message for the tts account with a sender not in the allowFrom list, it gets rejected. The user's open_id IS in the allowFrom list, so that should work, but maybe the routing logic is using the wrong session or there's a mismatch in how the account is being selected.\n\nI also notice there's a `agent:tts:main` session that was updated very recently (within seconds), which corresponds to when the user sent the \"still not working\" message. This suggests there might be multiple sessions or the timing of when the allowFrom was set versus when the session was created could be the problem.\n\nLooking at the most recent session list, there's no active Feishu session for the user, yet messages are still coming through to me. This tells me the Feishu → tts routing isn't happening at all—messages to the TK bot are somehow reaching me instead. The fact that `agent:tts:main` was updated at 1779537871917 (essentially right now) suggests the user might be testing something in the web UI, which would explain why the session is active but there's no corresponding Feishu direct session for the user's open_id.\n\nThe core problem is that when a user sends a message to the TK bot in Feishu, OpenClaw should route it to the tts agent, but instead it's going to me. This could be a webhook registration issue where the TK bot's events are being routed to the wrong endpoint, or there's a mismatch between how the message events are being interpreted versus the bot configuration.\n\nI should check if there's any active WebSocket connection handling the TK bot's events. Looking at the gateway process, it's using multiple HTTPS connections to various addresses, which suggests it's maintaining persistent connections. Let me try sending a test message directly to the TK bot to see what happens—if it lands in my session instead of the tts session, that confirms the routing is broken.\n\nWait, I need to clarify something from the user's statement. They said the TK bot works fine in the OpenClaw web UI but fails in Feishu. So the bot itself is functioning properly, just not receiving Feishu messages. This means the problem is likely in how Feishu events are being routed to the correct session or handler.\n\nI'm wondering if the issue could be with the websocket connections themselves. Both kiit and tts bots are using the same connection mode (websocket, inherited globally), but that shouldn't prevent them from both maintaining active connections. Let me reconsider what else could cause only the tts bot to fail while kiit works.\n\nActually, I think the core problem might be that when a user sends a message to the TK 选品大师 bot in Feishu, the message never makes it to the tts agent at all—it either gets lost or gets routed elsewhere. That would explain why there's no response. Let me try sending a test message directly to the TK bot through the tts agent to see if I can even reach it.\n\nBut wait, that approach has a problem: I'm sending from the kiit session, which means it'll go through the kiit agent, not as a genuine Feishu DM to the TK bot. That won't actually tell me whether the TK bot is properly connected to Feishu.\n\nMaybe I need to look at this from a completely different angle. If the user interacts with the TK bot through the web UI directly, that would explain why it works there—the web UI session is maintained separately from the Feishu integration. But if they're trying to reach it through Feishu, something in that connection path is broken.\n\nThe bot is bound to the correct Feishu app (cli_a930f78f51399bc6) and tkinter shows it as connected, yet Feishu messages aren't reaching it. I'm starting to wonder if the issue is that the TK bot doesn't have an active Feishu session for this specific user—there's no `agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb` session on file, only an older one for a different user. So when the message arrives, the routing might be failing because there's no established session to route it to.\n\nThe last activity was 1779537871917 (just seconds ago) on tts:main (web UI), but that's not a Feishu session. When the user sends a message via Feishu to the TK bot, the system needs to create a new session or find an existing one, and if the routing logic depends on a specific session existing, that could be the breakdown.\n\nI'm wondering if the problem might be a workspace mismatch. The tts agent's config points to `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/Selector`, but the actual workspace for tts is at `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace-tts`. That inconsistency could be preventing the agent from functioning properly when handling Feishu messages.\n\nThe model configuration also seems off—the agent defaults to `gemini/gemini-2.0-flash` while the global config specifies `minimax/MiniMax-M2.7`. These kinds of configuration conflicts could easily cause the bot to fail silently when processing incoming messages.\n\nThe routing mechanism itself is unclear. I'm not sure how OpenClaw maps incoming Feishu messages to the correct account and agent—the websocket connections for kiit and tts are separate, so there must be some logic that matches incoming events to the right handler.\n\nLet me try checking the actual WebSocket connections to see if both accounts are truly connected. I notice the system shows kiit as the defaultFeishuAccount, but tts is configured separately. I'm wondering if the routing uses the app_id from the message itself to look up the account, and if tts doesn't have explicit routing configured, it might fall back to defaulting to the main kiit session. That could explain why messages to tts are being processed through the main session instead.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the defaultAccount setting only determines which account to use for outgoing messages—not incoming ones. For routing incoming messages, OpenClaw must be looking at the message's app_id to find the matching account. Since Feishu delivers messages to the webhook with the bot's credentials embedded, the system should extract that app_id and match it to the correct account. So if the message is for tts (app_id cli_a930f78f51399bc6), it should route to the tts account.\n\nThe fact that tts has no routes configured suggests OpenClaw is finding the account by app_id alone, without needing explicit route entries. So the issue might be something else entirely—maybe the message isn't actually reaching the tts account, or the session creation for tts is failing for some reason.\n\nLet me check if there's a recent sessions file that was updated, and also try a different diagnostic approach—maybe sending a test message directly to the user through tts to see if the account is actually functional.\n\nActually, the most straightforward test would be to have the user send a direct message to the TK bot in Feishu and see if it responds. The fact that the web UI works but Feishu doesn't suggests the issue is specifically with how Feishu messages are being routed or processed, not with the bot's overall connectivity. The TK bot uses a different app_id (cli_a930f78f51399bc6) than the default kiit bot (cli_a93650c6fc785bce), so when a user sends a message to TK in Feishu, it goes to TK's webhook endpoint. OpenClaw receives it there, looks up the account by app_id, and routes to the tts agent. This should work, but I notice the account has `allowFrom: [\"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"]` and `dmPolicy: allowlist` configured, so maybe there's something else going on with how the routing is actually happening.\n\nLet me think about whether the tts agent is even processing messages correctly. The most recent session shows `agent:tts:main` with an update timestamp of around 1779537871917 milliseconds, which is about 11 hours ago from the current time. That session might be from the web UI rather than Feishu, but it's concerning that there's no active Feishu session for the current user if they just tried messaging the bot. I should try sending a test message directly to the TK bot to see what happens.\n\nWait, I realize I can use the Feishu API to send a message directly to the user from the TK bot's account. This would help me verify whether the TK bot can actually send messages to the user—if the API call succeeds, the bot has the right permissions and the issue is likely on the receiving end. If it fails, the problem might be with the bot's send capabilities or the token itself.\n\nBut there's a simpler approach I should try first. I need to check if the TK bot is actively connected to the OpenClaw gateway using a diagnostic command. Let me run that to see what's actually happening with the connection.\n\nI also want to verify the current configuration is correct—specifically checking the allowFrom list and dmPolicy settings to confirm they're properly configured.\n","thinkingSignature":"e10cdf6b971d5bae26c5209e40a6a91b4391867bcdafb61690389bdb4ff6eae5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ni5lbm8pd7aq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\ntts = cfg['channels']['feishu']['accounts']['tts']\nkiit = cfg['channels']['feishu']['accounts']['kiit']\n\nprint('=== TK 选品大师 (tts) ===')\nprint(f'appId: {tts[\\\"appId\\\"]}')\nprint(f'enabled: {tts[\\\"enabled\\\"]}')\nprint(f'allowFrom: {tts.get(\\\"allowFrom\\\")}')\nprint(f'dmPolicy: {tts.get(\\\"dmPolicy\\\")}')\nprint(f'connectionMode: {tts.get(\\\"connectionMode\\\", \\\"inherit from global\\\")}')\nprint()\n\nprint('=== KIIT (kiit) ===')\nprint(f'appId: {kiit[\\\"appId\\\"]}')\nprint(f'enabled: {kiit[\\\"enabled\\\"]}')\nprint(f'allowFrom: {kiit.get(\\\"allowFrom\\\")}')\nprint(f'dmPolicy: {kiit.get(\\\"dmPolicy\\\")}')\nprint()\n\nprint('=== 全局 ===')\nprint(f'connectionMode: {cfg[\\\"channels\\\"][\\\"feishu\\\"].get(\\\"connectionMode\\\")}')\nprint(f'defaultAccount: {cfg[\\\"channels\\\"][\\\"feishu\\\"].get(\\\"defaultAccount\\\")}')\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":492,"output":2786,"cacheRead":93794,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97072,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cache