{"type":"message","id":"bcbe6e55","parentId":"bbb0fd87","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:10:09.980Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The last message in the tts session shows an empty content with an error:\n```\n\"Message role=assistant, content=[], ... \"stopReason\":\"error\",\"errorMessage\":\"{\\\"type\\\":\\\"error\\\",\\\"error\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"overloaded_error\\\",\\\"message\\\":\\\"server is busy, please retry later\\\"}}\"\n```\n\nSo the tts agent crashed with \"server is busy, please retry later\" during the cron run. This might have left the session in a bad state. But more importantly - the session `agent:tts:main` has `updatedAt=1779537871917`. Let me convert that timestamp.\n\n1779537871917 ms = 1779537871.917 seconds\nActually that's a very large number - let me check: 1779537871917 / 1000 = 1779537871.917 seconds from epoch\nThat's about 56 years from 1970... wait no.\n\nActually 1779537871917 is much larger than current Unix timestamps (which are around 1.7 billion for 2026). Wait:\n- Current time in seconds: ~1.779e9 (May 2026)\n- 1779537871917 ms = 1779537871.917 seconds - that's current time! ✓\n\nSo updatedAt = 1779537871917 ms = Sat May 23 2026 20:04:31 GMT+8 (approximately). This is basically NOW (the current session).\n\nSo there's an active tts session (agent:tts:main) that was last updated at 20:04:31 today. But the user's messages to TK 选品大师 from today don't seem to have created a new session.\n\nWait - `agent:tts:main` might be the web chat session (OpenClaw's own web UI), NOT the Feishu DM session. Looking at the origin:\n\n\n`origin: {'provider': 'webchat', 'surface': 'webchat', 'chatType': 'direct'}`\n\nYes - that's the web UI session. So the tts agent is running fine in the web UI, but Feishu DM messages aren't creating a corresponding Feishu session for tts. There should be a session like `agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb` if the user's Feishu messages were being routed to tts, but that doesn't exist in the sessions.json.\n\nThe user says they're messaging TK 选品大师 directly and getting no response, only an empty reply. But from OpenClaw's perspective, those messages should be creating a Feishu DM session with tts if they're being routed correctly. Since there's no such session in sessions.json, either the messages aren't reaching tts at all, or they're being handled differently than expected.\n\nThe tts account's allowFrom and dmPolicy are set correctly, and it's running on websocket like kiit, so the issue isn't configuration. The problem must be at the Feishu webhook level - when the user sends a message to the TK bot, Feishu might not be delivering it to OpenClaw's webhook, or OpenClaw isn't processing it correctly. I'm not sure how to test this without more access to the system logs.\n\nI should ask the user directly if they've actually tried sending a message to the TK bot after our recent fix, since they mentioned \"还是不行\" but it's unclear if that's from earlier testing or current testing. Looking at the timestamps, the last cron run was at 09:00 this morning with an overloaded error at 09:02, so the bot was definitely active today. The user could be testing via web UI and getting responses, but Feishu messages aren't getting through. Let me ask them to clarify whether they're testing via Feishu or web UI right now.\n","thinkingSignature":"0bc48ad89ec216a7fc37fdb9e370007b787a9ae2fbb0f843c02a91a64ff5eb63"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mhesxkibokt8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -30 /home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/sessions/e93a01b9-8c85-4f1d-89f5-5a4af2771503.jsonl 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    line = line.strip()\n    if not line: continue\n    try:\n        obj = json.loads(line)\n        if obj.get('type') == 'message':\n            msg = obj.get('message', {})\n            role = msg.get('role')\n            ts = obj.get('timestamp','')\n            content = msg.get('content', [])\n            if isinstance(content, list) and content:\n                text = str(content[0])[:300] if isinstance(content[0], dict) else str(content[0])\n            else:\n                text = str(content)[:300]\n            print(f'[{ts}] role={role}: {text}')\n    except: pass\n\" 2>/dev/null | tail -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":601,"output":1035,"cacheRead":94748,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96384,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779538187175,"responseId":"0660cc0c3efdd691c63e215ea8f435bd"}}
