{"type":"message","id":"8b35218a","parentId":"6821d2bf","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:11:36.577Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_c46m91tucs0l_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-05-10\n\n## Agent 团队配置完成\n\n完成了全量 Agent 团队（10 个）的配置，所有 Bot 均已绑定独立飞书账号：\n\n- main (KIIT) → kiit\n- tts → tts\n- agent-orchestrator → agent-orchestrator\n- content → content\n- koc → koc\n- traffic → traffic\n- ops → ops\n- director → director\n- finance → finance\n- review → review\n\n同步更新了 AGENTS.md 和 MEMORY.md 中的团队信息和任务分配映射。"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":36,"aggregated":"# 2026-05-10\n\n## Agent 团队配置完成\n\n完成了全量 Agent 团队（10 个）的配置，所有 Bot 均已绑定独立飞书账号：\n\n- main (KIIT) → kiit\n- tts → tts\n- agent-orchestrator → agent-orchestrator\n- content → content\n- koc → koc\n- traffic → traffic\n- ops → ops\n- director → director\n- finance → finance\n- review → review\n\n同步更新了 AGENTS.md 和 MEMORY.md 中的团队信息和任务分配映射。","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779538296574}}
{"type":"message","id":"347a7a50","parentId":"8b35218a","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:12:00.820Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the config looks correct. Let me think about what else could be wrong.\n\nActually, let me try something - let me check the gateway logs more carefully to see if there are any clues about why messages to tts aren't getting through.\n\nLet me also try to directly send a message to the tts bot via the message tool to see if that works.\n\nActually wait - the user is saying that from the web UI, the tts bot CAN reply. The web UI has a built-in chat interface for each agent. When the user uses the web UI to chat with tts, it works. But when the user goes to the FEISHU app and sends a message to the TK 选品大师 bot (which is a Feishu bot with app_id cli_a930f78f51399bc6), there is no reply.\n\nThis means:\n1. The tts agent itself works fine (web UI works)\n2. The Feishu bot account (cli_a930f78f51399bc6) is receiving messages from the user\n3. But those messages aren't being routed to the tts agent in OpenClaw\n\nThis strongly suggests the issue is at the Feishu message reception/routing level in OpenClaw. \n\nLet me think about what could cause this:\n\n1. When Feishu delivers a message for app_id `cli_a930f78f51399bc6`, OpenClaw receives it via webhook or websocket. But if the connection isn't properly handling multiple accounts, the message might not get routed.\n\n2. Actually wait - I should check the gateway status more carefully. Let me see if the tts websocket connection is active.\n\nBut actually the tts session exists and cron works, so the tts websocket connection must be working. Unless the cron is triggering via a different mechanism (like a task scheduler that's separate from the Feishu message handling).\n\nLet me think... Actually, I have an idea. Let me check if maybe there's a mismatch between the Feishu app's webhook verification token and what's configured. But we don't have access to see the actual webhook config from the Feishu side.\n \nWait, I just realized something important. Looking at those search results from yesterday, there was an ou_11f95142ee4622f42acc029c870f68bb open_id which is NOT the user's open_id. That's a different user. So maybe those messages in the search were the USER testing the TK bot and getting replies, but the user is now telling me it doesn't work? Or maybe those messages were from a DIFFERENT person testing the bot? The user's open_id is ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb and those messages from May 22 at 20:35 and earlier were sent to ou_11f95142ee4622f42acc029c870f68bb, which is different. So the user might be testing the bot with a different account or there's a different issue altogether.\n\nActually wait - I should look at those messages more carefully. They seem to be from the kiit bot, not the user asking about the TK bot. Let me think about what's actually happening here. The user says \"选品大师发消息有问题\" and \"在openclaw自身的webui后台是可以回复的\". So the TK bot works in the OpenClaw web UI but NOT in Feishu. This means the tts agent works fine, the issue is purely at the Feishu message reception level.\n\nSo what could be wrong? Let me think about what happens when a user sends a message to the TK bot in Feishu: Feishu delivers the message to the app's webhook, OpenClaw receives it, it routes to the correct account based on app_id, then to the correct agent. I added allowFrom and dmPolicy and restarted, but it's still not working. The only thing I can think of is that there's something about the allowFrom that's not quite right. Let me check what allowFrom actually does in OpenClaw.\n\nActually, I'm realizing something important from the sessions.json. The most recent tts session (updatedAt=1779537871917) is from \"webchat\" not from Feishu. This means the user has been chatting with tts via the OpenClaw web UI (webchat), not via Feishu DM. There's no recent Feishu DM session for tts! Even though we can see that tts's cron ran today at 9AM and the user has been chatting via the web UI, there's no record of any Feishu DM sessions for tts from today. This strongly suggests that Feishu messages to the TK bot are NOT being received or processed by OpenClaw at all. The tts Feishu session (agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68) has an old updatedAt from May 18, which indicates Feishu messages to tts haven't been working for a while.\n\nNow I need to check the gateway logs to see what's happening with these Feishu messages.\n","thinkingSignature":"be33d45921ff1cadf1b805b8482103ad78d5d718d49b961c430665d02e8229b2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_crjyw3wscpgk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -n 500 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"feishu\\|cli_a930\\|tts\" | tail -40","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":649,"output":1135,"cacheRead":97681,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99465,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779538296884,"responseId":"0660cc7925a1353983a6288ef1d836c5"}}
