{"type":"message","id":"51b1cba2","parentId":"9623fad3","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:13:28.874Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Journalctl isn't showing the detailed Feishu connection logs. Let me try to check OpenClaw's web status page or use the browser to look at the status dashboard. But the user already showed me a screenshot of the status page which said the bot is properly configured.\n\nLet me think about what could actually be wrong. The user says:\n1. The bot is properly bound in the OpenClaw webUI\n2. dmPolicy is allowlist and allowFrom contains the user's open_id\n3. The cron job works fine (tts agent is active)\n4. But when the user sends a DM to the TK bot in Feishu, no response\n\nThe key question: **When the user sends a DM to the TK bot, does Feishu actually deliver the message to OpenClaw?**\n\nIf Feishu is not delivering the message, the issue is on the Feishu app configuration side. If Feishu IS delivering it but OpenClaw is routing it to the wrong place, the issue is in OpenClaw.\n\nLet me try a different approach - let me check if there's any Feishu API endpoint we can call to verify the bot's webhook/event subscription status.\n\nActually, the most direct diagnostic: ask the user to look at the TK bot's Feishu app settings and check:\n1. Is the app using webhook or long polling?\n2. Is the event subscription URL pointing to the correct OpenClaw endpoint?\n3. Is the app in \"enabled\" state in Feishu's app console?\n\nBut I think I should try another diagnostic first. Let me check if there's a way to directly send a test message to the TK bot to see if it works.\n\nActually, I can try to use the message tool to send a message AS the TK bot to the user. But wait, that's sending FROM the bot, not receiving. But it would at least verify the bot's token is valid.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The user says:\n- All other agents work fine (can send/receive messages)\n\n\n- Only TK 选品大师 (tts) doesn't respond to DMs\n\nThis strongly suggests the issue is account-specific for the tts account. But we've confirmed: tts account is enabled, has allowFrom with the user's open_id, dmPolicy is allowlist. So the config looks correct. The problem might be that the Feishu app for TK bot (cli_a930f78f51399bc6) has the event subscription pointing to a different endpoint or uses a different message接收方式 than what OpenClaw expects.\n\nLet me try checking the actual Feishu app configuration for TK bot through the Feishu API, or use the OpenClaw CLI to diagnose the tts account's connection status.\n","thinkingSignature":"7f5792faf7e3b9b0677ff3eea7f0e528b36ea3e1bd53f5ddcf725f7314be6f07"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ud1mlb9cck49_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/halei/.openclaw && openclaw status 2>&1 | head -40 &\nsleep 3\nkill %1 2>/dev/null\nwait 2>/dev/null","timeout":8}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ud1mlb9cck49_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:18789/api/status 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -60 || echo \"No status endpoint\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":93,"output":709,"cacheRead":99131,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99933,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779538396176,"responseId":"0660ccdc6853f1c4f37985717051fd3b"}}
