{"type":"message","id":"fe0d5e4c","parentId":"7237fb92","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:14:15.053Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The openclaw status command timed out (it's a TUI application that needs a terminal). Let me try a different approach - let me directly check if the tts bot is connected by looking at its sessions and checking the Feishu API call logs.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The user says that TK 选品大师 works in the OpenClaw web UI but not in Feishu. This is very strange because the OpenClaw web UI uses the same backend - the web UI and Feishu should both route through the same tts agent.\n\nWait - I just realized something. When the user says \"选品大师子在openclaw自身的webui后台是可以回复的\", they might mean something different. Let me look at what this means:\n\nThe OpenClaw web UI (clawpanel) has a chat interface where you can select different agents. The user might be testing the TK 选品大师 agent via the web UI and getting replies. If the web UI works, it means the tts agent itself is functioning correctly.\n\nBut in Feishu, when the user sends a message to the TK bot (app_id cli_a930f78f51399bc6), there's no reply.\n\nThis suggests the problem is in the Feishu-to-tts routing, not in the tts agent itself.\n\nLet me check if there's an issue with the Feishu connection for the tts account. The tts account uses websocket mode (inherited from global). In websocket mode, OpenClaw maintains a persistent WebSocket connection to Feishu's server to receive events (messages) in real-time.\n\nIf the tts bot's websocket connection is active, messages should be received and routed to the tts agent.\n\nBut wait - if the tts agent works in the web UI, that means the agent is running and can process tasks. The cron job ran successfully this morning at 9AM. So the tts agent is functioning.\n\nThe issue is that incoming Feishu messages for the tts bot are not being delivered to the tts agent.\n\n\nI need to find if there's something sp