{"type":"message","id":"57bd5f34","parentId":"30af51e3","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:16:32.686Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see clearly - the user sent this message from their own open_id (ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb) and the message is coming through the kiit conversation. They're saying \"清楚了吗\" - meaning they've confirmed the situation and are asking if I understand now.\n\nThe user's latest message is from the kiit conversation - they're asking if I now understand the problem clearly. They said \"清楚了吗\" (Is it clear now?) after I asked them to check the TK bot's configuration in Feishu's open platform.\n\nLet me take a step back and think about this more carefully.\n\nThe user said earlier that:\n1. They sent a message to TK 选品大师 in Feishu\n2. No reply came back\n3. All other agents work\n4. Only TK 选品大师 doesn't respond to Feishu messages (but works in OpenClaw's own webUI)\n\nNow the user is saying \"清楚了吗\" - they want to know if I understand the problem.\n\nLet me think about what I know now:\n1. The user sends a message to TK bot in Feishu (app_id cli_a930f78f51399bc6)\n2. The message doesn't get a reply\n3. The user has NO tts session for their open_id\n4. The tts account's Feishu connection might not be working properly\n\nThe key insight is: when the user sends a message to TK bot, Feishu delivers it to the app. The app is connected via websocket to OpenClaw. OpenClaw should route it to the tts agent. But something is broken.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. I was asking the user to check the TK bot's configuration in Feishu's open platform. But the user's response \"清楚了吗\" sounds like they're tired of me asking questions and want me to just fix it.\n\nLet me look at this from a completely different angle. I know the tts account has `allowFrom` and `dmPolicy` set correctly now. \n\nThe tts agent has no Feishu session for the user, while the kiit agent is actively receiving messages. This suggests the TK bot's websocket connection to Feishu might be broken or disconnected, even though the kiit connection works fine. Maybe the kiit account is maintaining its connection while the tts account isn't properly connected to Feishu's servers.\n\nActually, I think I see the issue now. Looking at the sessions.json, the tts agent shows `accountId: None` for both the main and cron sessions, but the feishu session does have `accountId: tts`. The feishu session is from an old user (ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68), not the current user. So the tts agent has an old Feishu connection but no active session for the current user, which would explain why messages aren't reaching the agent.\n\nBut wait - the feishu session's accountId is correctly set to 'tts', so messages sent to the TK bot should be routed to that account. The problem might be that the tts account's websocket connection to Feishu isn't active, or the allowFrom/dmPolicy settings aren't being checked properly. I think the next step is to check whether the TK bot's Feishu app has the right event subscriptions enabled.\n\nLet me try a different approach - checking the OpenClaw gateway's Feishu connection status directly to see if the TK bot is even connected.\n\nActually, I should verify the WebSocket connections. Looking at the journalctl output, I only see references to `feishu[default]`, not `feishu[tts]`. If the tts account were properly connected, there should be separate log entries for it. This suggests the tts bot's WebSocket connection might not be established at all.\n\nLet me check what the `/feishu/events` webhook handler does when a message arrives, since that might be where the routing is failing.\n\nWait - I think I've been misunderstanding the connection mode. The `connectionMode: websocket` at the global Feishu level means OpenClaw uses persistent WebSocket connections to Feishu's servers rather than short-lived webhook callbacks. Each bot app would maintain its own persistent connection this way.\n\nBut there's a problem with this setup. If OpenClaw creates one WebSocket connection per bot app, then the kiit and tts bots would have separate connections. However, if the tts account isn't properly configured or its connection is failing, messages might not be delivered to the tts bot while kiit continues working fine.\n\nI need to figure out why the tts connection might be failing while kiit is fine. Looking at the logs, I see kiit is processing messages, but there's nothing similar for tts. The kiit account uses `cli_a93650c6fc785bce` and kiit is working, so the OpenClaw gateway itself is functioning. The tts account uses `cli_a930f78f51399bc6` and isn't working. Both are using the same global websocket mode, so the issue isn't the connection method itself - it's specific to the tts account's connection or configuration.\n\nThe tts account's WebSocket connection to Feishu might have dropped or never established properly, or the Feishu app for tts might have been disabled or had its permissions changed. I should ask the user to verify the TK bot's connection status in Feishu's open platform, or restart the gateway to force reconnection of all accounts. The user seems frustrated with my questions, so I should be more direct about what I'm seeing and what needs to be checked.\n\nThe real issue might be that the tts account is using its own WebSocket connection to Feishu while kiit uses the global connection. When the user sends a message to the TK bot in Feishu, the message goes to the app but never arrives at OpenClaw because the WebSocket isn't properly connected. The cron job working doesn't necessarily mean the WebSocket is active - it could be that cron jobs use a different mechanism to send notifications. I should check if the tts agent is actually receiving and processing messages through Feishu's event system.\n\nThe cron job triggers the tts agent, which then uses the feishu_im_user_message tool to send results back to the user. This works because the tool uses the user's credentials, not the tts bot's WebSocket connection. So the cron job succeeds through a different delivery method, but direct user messages to the tts bot rely on the WebSocket being active - which explains why they're not getting through. The fix likely involves restarting the gateway to re-establish the tts account's WebSocket connection.\n\nBut I'm wondering if there's a deeper issue with how multiple bot accounts are handled. Each Feishu bot app maintains its own connection, and they can all be active simultaneously since they're separate apps. The real problem might be that when Feishu sends events for the tts bot, something's going wrong in how those events are being routed or processed. I should check the OpenClaw logs to see what happens when the user sends a message to the TK bot - there might be an error or routing issue I'm missing.\n\nActually, I think I've found it. When the user sends a message to the TK bot in Feishu and no session exists yet, OpenClaw creates a new session. But if the allowFrom check is failing - maybe because the policy says \"allowlist\" but the user isn't being recognized properly - then the message gets rejected before it can even create a session. I need to look at the actual session creation logic in OpenClaw to confirm this.\n\nThe user is frustrated because they've already confirmed the app_id and I'm still asking questions instead of fixing it. I should stop and just tell them what I've found and what I'm going to do about it.\n\nSo here's what's happening: the TK bot has no active Feishu session for the user, even though the account config looks correct. The most likely cause is that the TK bot's WebSocket connection to Feishu dropped. I'm going to restart the gateway to force all bot connections to re-establish - this should fix it. If it doesn't, then the problem is in Feishu's app configuration for the TK bot, and we'll need to check the event subscriptions there.\n","thinkingSignature":"2cd09882542e5e0338610cb7afc66b6f3881e16af655e4386f4037d856760601"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nTK bot 没有收到任何消息——你的 open_id 根本没有分配到 tts 会话。问题很可能是 **TK 选品大师的 WebSocket 连接断开了**（cron 能发出去是因为用了用户身份的消息接口，不依赖 bot 的 ws）。\n\n我来重启 gateway 强制重连所有 bot 的 WebSocket：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h6zuqod6kruo_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"restart","note":"重启后验证 TK 选品大师 是否重新建立了 Feishu WebSocket 连接","reason":"TK 选品大师的飞书 WebSocket 连接疑似断开，消息无法送达。重启强制重连。"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":373,"output":1882,"cacheRead":101244,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":103499,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779538561661,"responseId":"0660cd82cda1db008a0dcca39a5d6f78"}}
