{"type":"message","id":"eb90b246","parentId":"8b2e2173","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:17:02.193Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user's tts session still doesn't exist after restart. This is very strange - the tts account should receive messages from the user and create a session. But there's no session for ou_f590c429.\n\nActually, wait - I should think about this differently. The `agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` session has `accountId: tts`, which means it was correctly routed to the tts account. This confirms that the tts account CAN receive Feishu messages.\n\nBut why doesn't the user's current messages create a session? The user is saying they send a message to the TK bot and get no reply. After our config fix (allowFrom + dmPolicy), it still doesn't work.\n\nLet me think about what could be different:\n1. The user might be sending messages to the kiit bot, not the tts bot\n2. The tts bot's Feishu app might have been uninstalled or disabled\n3. The tts bot's websocket connection might not be receiving events\n\nActually, wait. I just realized something. When I searched the user's messages earlier, I found:\n\nThe user's messages about \"5.20版本\" were received by kiit (not tts), and those messages appear in the kiit conversation with me. But the user is saying they sent the message to \"选品大师\" which should be the tts bot.\n\nBut actually - the user's open_id is ou_f590c429. The messages that appear in the kiit conversation came from ou_f590c429. The user might have sent the message to kiit (by mistake) and is confused about why tts doesn't respond.\n\nBut the user is very clear: they say \"对，2发过去无任何回复， 所有的agent都正常，只有这个没有回复\". They know which bot they're messaging.\n\nOK let me think about the architecture again. \n\nWhen a user sends a DM to a Feishu bot, Feishu routes that message to a specific app's webhook or persistent connection. The gateway then creates a new session for that app. Looking at the `sessions.json` for tts, there's a session for ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 - so the tts bot has received messages before. But the current user's messages aren't creating a session. This suggests either the tts bot's connection isn't receiving the new messages, or the user is actually messaging a different bot.\n\nThe user's statement \"所有的agent都正常，只有这个没有回复\" means all agents work fine, which suggests they're correctly messaging each bot. But if that were true, the tts session would already exist. So either the tts bot's websocket connection dropped and isn't receiving new events, or there's a routing issue where the messages are going somewhere else. Let me check if the kiit sessions.json shows any messages from this user - that would indicate if they're accidentally messaging kiit instead.\n\nLooking at the message history from today, I see the user sent messages to kiit today, but there's no evidence they've actually sent a message to tts yet. The user said \"还是不行\" after my fix, which could mean they tested and it still failed, or they're referring to yesterday's issue. Let me verify whether the user has even attempted to send a message to tts since our changes, or if they're only testing kiit and assuming tts would behave the same way.\n\nThe core issue is that tts doesn't have a session for ou_f590c429, meaning the tts account has never received a message from this user. This could mean either the user never actually messaged tts after our fix, or the tts websocket is disconnected and not receiving events. I should ask the user to send a test message to tts right now and see if a session gets created, but first I need to check if the tts Feishu connection is even active.\n","thinkingSignature":"b0056fb0c5ba35559ce1e4e0c60e3f1781f5a30af1b1c44660d902b84c6b3949"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ok7pw4mg2wzv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -n 300 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep -iE \"tts|cli_a930|websocket.*account|account