{"type":"message","id":"efb2244b","parentId":"a86ffefe","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:17:25.440Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is very revealing! The gateway.log is from May 5th and May 15th, not from today. The most recent restart (May 22) doesn't seem to have been logged here. Let me check the gateway.err.log which might have newer logs.\n\nLooking at the May 5 log, I can see:\n- `feishu[kiit]: starting WebSocket connection...` - kiit connected via WS\n- `feishu[tts]: starting WebSocket connection...` - tts connected via WS  \n- Both got their bot open_id resolved:\n  - kiit: `ou_11f95142ee4622f42acc029c870f68bb`\n  - tts: `ou_09c92e096986a0fcd5b389561a0a1a84`\n\nSo the tts bot connected successfully on May 5. But this is old log. The current gateway process might have newer logs. Let me check if there are logs after May 22.\n\nWait - the restart on May 22 at 08:07 should have generated new log entries. But this gateway.log only has entries up to May 15. Maybe the current process logs to a different location? Or maybe the journalctl has the real-time logs.\n\n\nI should look at the gateway.err.log to see if there's more recent activity there.\n","thinkingSignature":"7a3acedc0cb94bbb65b04d3f750a02d6bf4579aa09a1beb11dfd5c484442c405"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2g4cnpibolwg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -100 /home/halei/.openclaw/logs/gateway.err.log 2>/dev/null | tail -50","timeout":5}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2g4cnpibolwg_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/halei/.openclaw/logs/stability/ 2>/dev/null","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3332,"output":391,"cacheRead":102664,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":106387,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779538635019,"responseId":"0660cdcc793bd9786a82803cda3ff7c2"}}
