{"type":"message","id":"0c6a8edb","parentId":"c8e461b8","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:21:17.295Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No status endpoint. Let me try a different approach - send a test message to the tts agent via session send to check if it responds. Actually that's blocked. Let me think differently.\n\nThe key issue: user confirms the TK bot has the right app_id. All other agents' bots work. Only TK doesn't.\n\nThis means TK's Feishu WebSocket connection is likely broken. The OpenClaw gateway maintains persistent WebSocket connections to Feishu's servers for each bot app. If TK's connection is dead while others are alive, messages to TK won't be received.\n\nLet me check if there are any recent connection status logs. Actually, let me check the health monitoring.\n","thinkingSignature":"9b5cec175dbf12e43a21875a75c9c5c902c0efa67a7faeaeec1063f980628ffa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hrfns7oicvyz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/.openclaw/logs/config-health.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":125,"output":202,"cacheRead":71744,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72071,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779538872418,"responseId":"0660ceb8530b26046400bb9ca3fef64b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"85ce7a5d","parentId":"0c6a8edb","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:21:17.525Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hrfns7oicvyz_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n    \"entries\": {\n        \"/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json\": {\n            \"lastKnownGood\": {\n                \"hash\": \"9dd6e11fe4cea7a3f83783be51db0052da636a188ef66dbbd215221e7364994e\",\n                \"bytes\": 29459,\n                \"mtimeMs\": 1779502402150.0813,\n                \"ctimeMs\": 1779502402155.0813,\n                \"dev\": \"66306\",\n                \"ino\": \"7209493\",\n                \"mode\": 384,\n                \"nlink\": 1,\n                \"uid\": 1000,\n                \"gid\": 1000,\n                \"hasMeta\": true,\n                \"gatewayMode\": \"local\",\n                \"observedAt\": \"2026-05-23T12:02:55.797Z\"\n            },\n            \"lastPromotedGood\": {\n                \"hash\": \"9dd6e11fe4cea7a3f83783be51db0052da636a188ef66dbbd215221e7364994e\",\n                \"bytes\": 29459,\n                \"mtimeMs\": 1779502402150.0813,\n                \"ctimeMs\": 1779502402155.0813,\n                \"dev\": \"66306\",\n                \"ino\": \"7209493\",\n                \"mode\": 33152,\n                \"nlink\": 1,\n                \"uid\": 1000,\n                \"gid\": 1000,\n                \"hasMeta\": true,\n                \"gatewayMode\": \"local\",\n                \"observedAt\": \"2026-05-23T02:23:54.174Z\"\n            },\n            \"lastObservedSuspiciousSignature\": null\n        }\n    }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":70,"aggregated":"{\n    \"entries\": {\n        \"/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json\": {\n            \"lastKnownGood\": {\n                \"hash\": \"9dd6e11fe4cea7a3f83783be51db0052da636a188ef66dbbd215221e7364994e\",\n                \"bytes\": 29459,\n                \"mtimeMs\": 1779502402150.0813,\n                \"ctimeMs\": 1779502402155.0813,\n                \"dev\": \"66306\",\n                \"ino\": \"7209493\",\n                \"mode\": 384,\n                \"nlink\": 1,\n                \"uid\": 1000,\n                \"gid\": 1000,\n                \"hasMeta\": true,\n                \"gatewayMode\": \"local\",\n                \"observedAt\": \"2026-05-23T12:02:55.797Z\"\n            },\n            \"lastPromotedGood\": {\n                \"hash\": \"9dd6e11fe4cea7a3f83783be51db0052da636a188ef66dbbd215221e7364994e\",\n                \"bytes\": 29459,\n                \"mtimeMs\": 1779502402150.0813,\n                \"ctimeMs\": 1779502402155.0813,\n                \"dev\": \"66306\",\n                \"ino\": \"7209493\",\n                \"mode\": 33152,\n                \"nlink\": 1,\n                \"uid\": 1000,\n                \"gid\": 1000,\n                \"hasMeta\": true,\n                \"gatewayMode\": \"local\",\n                \"observedAt\": \"2026-05-23T02:23:54.174Z\"\n            },\n            \"lastObservedSuspiciousSignature\": null\n        }\n    }\n}","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779538877522}}
{"type":"message","id":"bbc5410d","parentId":"85ce7a5d","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:21:27.899Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so config health is good - no suspicious changes. The config hasn't been tampered with.\n\nLet me think about this problem again. The user confirmed:\n1. The app_id in Feishu for TK is `cli_a930f78f51399bc6` ✓\n2. All other bots work in Feishu\n3. Only TK doesn't respond\n\nThe config is correct. The app_id is confirmed. But messages don't get responses.\n\nWhat could cause this? The tts account is configured correctly. Its WebSocket should be connected. But messages to it don't get responses.\n\nWait - I just thought of something. Let me check if the issue might be with the **Feishu app's event subscription**. Even though the config is correct, if TK's app in Feishu's developer console doesn't have the right event subscriptions, messages won't be delivered.\n\nActually, the user has already confirmed the app_id is correct. So the Feishu app is the right one. But if the event subscription is wrong, messages wouldn't arrive via webhook. But we're using websocket mode, which doesn't rely on webhook...\n\nActually, wait. In WebSocket mode for Feishu bots, the app still needs to have the event subscriptions configured. The WebSocket connection is for receiving events that the app is subscribed to. If the app doesn't subscribe to `im.message.receive_v1`, it won't receive messages via WebSocket.\n\nBut in 5/5's logs, I saw:\n```\nfeishu[tts]: starting WebSocket connection...\n  'receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app, Configured in:\\n' +\n    '        Receive events/callbacks through persistent connection(使用 长连接 接收事件/回调)'\n\n\n```\n\nThis suggests that in WebSocket mode, OpenClaw is using Feishu's Long Connection (长连接) capability. For this to work, the app needs to be configured to use long connection for receiving events. But this is a Feishu app-level configuration (in the Feishu developer console), not an OpenClaw config.\n\nThe message \"receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app\" suggests this is a Feishu restriction - you can only use WebSocket/long-connection if you're a self-built Feishu app (自建应用). If the TK app was created as a different type, it might not support long connections.\n\nLooking at the log, both kiit and tts are using WebSocket mode and both show the same message about long connections, so they should both be properly configured for this. But if the WebSocket isn't actually connecting for tts, then the event subscriptions might not be available. Let me reconsider the architecture - kiit and tts might have different Feishu app configurations or permissions that affect their WebSocket capabilities. The WebSocket mode was set up on 5/5 and it's now 5/23. The gateway has restarted multiple times since then, which should have re-established the connections. When the gateway restarts, it restarts all feishu accounts. But I haven't seen tts-specific logs after the 5/15 restart. Let me check if there's a way to verify if the tts WebSocket is currently connected.\n\nActually, I wonder if the issue is simpler. Maybe the Feishu app's \"机器人\" (bot) capability was disabled or the app was put in some kind of suspended state. Or the event subscription for receiving messages was removed from the Feishu app configuration.\n\nI should suggest the user check:\n1. Feishu open platform → TK app → Basic Information → App status (is it normal/enabled?)\n2. Event subscriptions → Is \"Receive messages\" (接收消息) subscribed?\n3. Robot configuration → Is the bot feature enabled?\n\nBut wait, if the user confirms other bots work, those other bots presumably use the same Feishu app type. Unless the other bots use different Feishu apps that are properly configured.\n\nActually, looking at the config earlier: kiit uses cli_a93650c6fc785bce, content uses cli_a978060ba7249bd8, etc. Each agent has its own Feishu app. So if content works but TK doesn't, it means TK's specific Feishu app (cli_a930f78f51399bc6) has a problem while others are fine.\n\nThe most likely culprit is the TK app in Feishu's developer console has its event subscriptions removed or the bot was disabled. I should ask the user to verify this in the Feishu developer console.","thinkingSignature":"b20e104a9a1ee6caba1e4547c2acc7ceb00ac0253321325e718ab42bb63ae8ca"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6echi9llon4q_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -n 500 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep -iE \"feishu\\[tts\\]|feishu\\[.*tts.*\\]\" | tail -20","timeout":5}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6echi9llon4q_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -n 500 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep -iE \"websocket|WebSocket.*start|start.*WebSocket\" | grep -v \"openclaw\\|nodejs\\|clawpanel\" | tail -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":491,"output":1106,"cacheRead":71840,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73437,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779538877703,"responseId":"0660cebeea272fe7e72c250c31ffa209"}}
