{"type":"message","id":"a1c3cfae","parentId":"5d3d7d13","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:29:32.450Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see something interesting. The screenshot shows:\n- `agent:tts:main` - Age 22m, webchat, 75k/204k tokens\n\nBut the sessions.json shows `agent:tts:main` was last updated 24.6 minutes ago (which is close to 22m from the screenshot).\n\nThe key insight: `agent:tts:main` is a **webchat** session (web UI), not a feishu session. The user is viewing the tts agent in the web UI (clawpanel/openclaw dashboard). This is the OpenClaw Pi Default runtime.\n\nThe user is asking \"你看这个是不是有点奇诡\" - \"Does this look a bit strange to you?\"\n\nLooking at the dashboard:\n- `agent:main:main` - kiit main session, currently processing (there's a dot indicating active)\n- `agent:tts:main` - underlined in red, age 22m\n- Other agents: ops, content, etc.\n\nWhat's \"奇诡\" (strange/weird) here?\n\nThe `agent:tts:main` has:\n- Age: 22 minutes\n- Cache: 84%\n- 75k/204k tokens\n\nThe age of 22m is approximately when the user's 19:54 message was sent (which is now ~34 minutes ago based on current time ~20:28). So 22 minutes ago would be around 20:06, which doesn't match 19:54 exactly.\n\nWait - actually, looking at the sessions.json, `agent:tts:main` was updated 24.6 minutes ago. That would put it at around 20:04, which is close to 22m from the screenshot (time drift is normal).\n\n\nThe tts agent is online and responsive via webchat - it has an active session with recent token usage and good cache hit rates. The real issue is that the user is reporting Feishu DMs to tts aren't getting responses, but the web UI shows tts is actually processing and healthy. The 22 minute age aligns roughly with when the user messaged via Feishu, suggesting the message did reach tts but something's preventing it from responding back through Feishu.\n\nWhat's striking is that `agent:tts:main` is highlighted in red with the webchat session at 75k/204k tokens - this suggests the web UI is actively processing something, which could indicate the tts agent is occupied handling something else. This might explain why Feishu messages aren't getting through - if tts is already processing a request, it might not have capacity to handle new incoming messages.\n\nBut actually, the cron task finished at 09:00 UTC (17:00 local), which was over 3 hours ago, so the system shouldn't be that backlogged. Let me reconsider what the user is pointing out about the monitoring - they said \"你看这个是不是有点奇诡\" which suggests something specific about the tts agent's state that seems off. Maybe it's not about the age or backlog, but rather something about how the tts agent is registered or configured that appears wrong in the monitoring interface.\n\nThe `agent:tts:main` session is underlined in red in the monitoring, which could indicate a problem - perhaps an error state or something that shouldn't be happening. The user is probably noticing something in the screenshot that doesn't look right to them, and they're asking me to confirm whether this appears strange to me as well.\n","thinkingSignature":"842c8d68a56023b724ff9f40b7d4ebe7fdbe9bc76de31811e7ce6de0a7bcc967"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n是的，看到了。这个监控显示 `agent:tts:main` 年龄 22 分钟，高速缓存 84%，消耗 75k tokens。\n\n**你看到什么奇怪的地方吗？**\n\n22 分钟前大约是 20:06，你的消息是 19:54 发的。22 分钟和 19:54 的时间差说明 tts agent 在 20:06 左右有活动。但奇怪的是：\n\n- `agent:tts:main` 是 **webchat** 会话（OpenClaw web UI），不是飞书 DM 会话\n- 飞书 DM 没有对应的 session（`agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_f590c429` 不存在）\n- 但 tts 的 web UI session 在 22 分钟前有活动\n\n**这说明 tts agent 可能在 web UI 有东西在跑，但飞书消息没有触发新 session。**\n\n🎯 你说\"有点奇诡\"——你具体看到哪里觉得奇怪？是 tts 这个 session 的年龄？还是其他什么？\n\n另外问一下：你现在在 OpenClaw 后台（clawpanel）里看到 tts agent 正在处理什么吗？还是只是一个 idle 的 webchat session？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":477,"output":943,"cacheRead":75669,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77089,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cache