{"type":"message","id":"347f12c3","parentId":"42175a10","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:35:54.098Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK now I see the full picture:\n\n**KIIT account (default account in Feishu):**\n- appId: cli_a93650c6fc785bce\n- allowFrom: None (inherits from global: ou_f590c429...)\n- dmPolicy: None (inherits from global: allowlist)\n\n**Global:**\n- defaultAccount: kiit\n- allowFrom: ['ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb']\n- dmPolicy: allowlist\n\nSo KIIT inherits the allowFrom and dmPolicy from the global settings! That's why KIIT works - it inherits `allowFrom: ['ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb']` from the global config.\n\n\nNow for TK (tts): it has `allowFrom: None` and `dmPolicy: None` which means it doesn't inherit from global, but when I checked earlier I saw `allowFrom: ['ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb']` and `dmPolicy: allowlist` - so it looks like these values were set at some point but got lost, possibly due to a gateway restart reverting the configuration.\n","thinkingSignature":"122726ab6639b206cdd94fa20bcfc84c3a32db93a5e2de326e49e5f392211150"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aagyy3nkbcpp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A5 '\"tts\"' /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json | head -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":290,"output":317,"cacheRead":79200,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79807,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779539748590,"responseId":"0660d225d5c8d38dddbf448e35d70053"}}
