{"type":"message","id":"d812f18f","parentId":"d5062162","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:36:02.843Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Very interesting! The tts account has `connectionMode: \"websocket\"` explicitly set. But earlier the gateway.log showed both kiit and tts using websocket mode (inherited from global). Now I see tts has it explicitly set.\n\nBut I notice the tts account config does NOT have `allowFrom` or `dmPolicy` fields. Earlier I saw those were set, but now they're gone. This is very strange.\n\nWait - I need to re-read what I saw earlier. Let me think carefully:\n\nEarlier today, when I checked the config, I saw:\n```\nTK 选品大师 allowFrom: ['ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb']\nTK 选品大师 dmPolicy: allowlist\n\n\n```\n\nBut now:\n```\nTK 选品大师 allowFrom: None\nTK 选品大师 dmPolicy: None\n```\n\nThe config was modified between then and now. When did this happen? Looking at the summary `sum_e8984fb057a7778c` from earlier today:\n> tts账号配置已修复（allowFrom=['ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb'], dmPolicy=allowlist），gateway已重启。\n\nSo the config WAS fixed with allowFrom and dmPolicy. But now they're showing as None again. The user's question about whether their ID is \"main\" suggests they might be looking at the wrong account or configuration.\n\n```\n","thinkingSignature":"bdc141a21f47456be6899cfe5c4f381ebbc908b3809b3f162d1fcf5760c72fcb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uszgpp56h9zp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\nprint('=== 所有 feishu accounts 配置 ===')\nfor name, acc in cfg['channels']['feishu']['accounts'].items():\n    print(f'{name}:')\n    print(f'  appId: {acc.get(\\\"appId\\\")}')\n    print(f'  allowFrom: {acc.get(\\\"allowFrom\\\")}')\n    print(f'  dmPolicy: {acc.get(\\\"dmPolicy\\\")}')\n    print(f'  connectionMode: {acc.get(\\\"connectionMode\\\", \\\"inherit\\\")}')\n    print()\n\"","timeout"