{"type":"message","id":"818f2a53","parentId":"541c8a63","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:36:20.906Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture. All accounts (kiit, tts, agent-orchestrator, content, traffic, ops, director, finance, review, koc) inherit from the global config:\n- dmPolicy: allowlist\n- allowFrom: ['ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb']\n\nSo every bot should accept messages from ou_f590c429. That means the issue isn't a missing allowFrom on the tts account.\n\nBut wait - the global `appId` is `cli_a93650c6fc785bce` which is kiit's appId. And `defaultAccount` is `kiit`.\n\n\nThe global appId acts as a fallback when a bot's appId isn't configured, but each bot should have its own appId set. Looking at the gateway.log, both kiit and tts successfully established WebSocket connections on May 5th - tts connected at 21:48:47 with its own bot open_id (ou_09c92e096986a0fcd5b389561a0a1a84), which means tts does have its own appId configured. The real question is why Feishu DMs to tts aren't working if the bot identity is properly set up. The user confirmed they typed \"是不是\" but the question cut off - they're likely asking me to confirm something specific about the binding. Given the earlier context about the bot's ID being \"度搜\" and now this yes/no question about my ID being \"main\", I think they're questioning whether my identity is actually \"main\" or something else. The \"度搜\" reference is probably them pointing out that the binding shows a different name than what I should be using.\n","thinkingSignature":"c6cb42c4e1cc26461df5684a0ecf027fa2f6f07e0161ed67146f95dcac85bb59"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gu7peamo0riy_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\nagents = cfg.get('agents', {})\nprint('=== Agents 配置 ===')\nfor agent_id, agent_cfg in agents.items():\n    name = agent_cfg.get('identity', {}).get('name', '(no name)')\n    print(f'{agent_id}: {name}')\n    # Check channels\n    ch = agent_cfg.get('channels', {})\n    feishu = ch.get('feishu', {})\n    print(f'  feishu accountId: {feishu.get(\\\"accountId\\\")}')\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":409,"output":533,"cacheRead":80224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81166,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779539773907,"responseId":"0660d23ec2651cc09845e117ea79a746"}}
