{"type":"message","id":"0b80cad4","parentId":"21877be0","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:36:47.774Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see that ALL agents have `feishuAccount=None`. This means none of them have an explicit feishu account binding. The routing is done via the `routes` array or by message matching.\n\nWait, but we know messages from the user to the main agent DO work. How does that happen?\n\nLet me look at the routes configuration.\n","thinkingSignature":"bdf103e3db187528802876896382f3c7fedcd098535842fcd38e5c3a21e641b2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yg5wtqlaxva3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\nroutes = cfg.get('routes', [])\nprint(f'Routes: {len(routes)} entries')\nfor r in routes:\n    print(f'  match: {r.get(\\\"match\\\")}')\n    print(f'  agentId: {r.get(\\\"agentId\\\")}')\n    print()\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":418,"output":201,"cacheRead":81472,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82091,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779539802702,"responseId":"0660d25bc16404141e750340b7610b24"}}
