{"type":"message","id":"5c9ddfa2","parentId":"a56b7a84","timestamp":"2026-05-23T12:37:00.553Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There are 0 routes. So the routing is purely account-based. When a message comes from Feishu, OpenClaw looks at which account it's for (based on the app_id in the event), and routes to that account's agent.\n\nSo the flow for a DM to TK (cli_a930f78f51399bc6):\n1. Feishu sends the event to OpenClaw with app_id = cli_a930f78f51399bc6\n2. OpenClaw looks up the account with this appId → finds \"tts\" account\n3. Routes to the tts agent with the message\n\nThis should work correctly. The account mapping is correct (tts → cli_a930f78f51399bc6).\n\nBut the user says TK doesn't respond. The sessions.json shows no tts feishu session for the current user.\n\nNow the user asks \"不是，你的id是main吗\" - \"No, is your id main?\"\n\nHmm - maybe the user is asking about the routing. When a DM comes to TK, does it route to the \"tts\" agent or to \"main\"?\n\nWait - the user is asking if MY (KIIT's) id is \"main\". YES! KIIT's agentId is \"main\"! The main agent is KIIT.\n\nSo the user is pointing out that KIIT has agentId \"main\", and maybe there's some confusion in routing because of this.\n\nActually, let me re-read the routes config again. The routes are empty (0 entries). So there's no explicit routing. The feishu channel maps to accounts, and each account is mapped to an agent. For the tts account, the agentId should be \"tts\".\n\nLet me look at the accounts config more carefully - specifically the routing between account and agent.","thinkingSignature":"2a345d87c63ad58a2d7cabedf5e6fca7b8957cfe2cbd81c84b3516ae3dc314f6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kdpjy6rf8j3g_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\naccounts = cfg['channels']['feishu']['accounts']\ntts = accounts.get('tts', {})\nprint('tts account full config:')\nfor k, v in tts.items():\n    print(f'  {k}: {v}')\nprint()\n# Check if there's an agentId field in the account\nprint('agentId in tts:', tts.get('agentId'))\nprint()\n# Also check kiit\nkiit = accounts.get('kiit', {})\nprint('kiit account full config:')\nfor k, v in kiit.items():\n    print(f'  {k}: {v}')\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":180,"output":566,"cacheRead":81856,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82602,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779539808256,"responseId":"0660d2601dede270948f9cd464fc4a15"}}
