{"type":"message","id":"016ff1b1","parentId":"4675e5f5","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:04:09.233Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The tts account is completely gone from the config! When the user \"unbound\" it from the management panel, it seems like the management panel deleted the tts account from the config entirely.\n\nI need to add the tts account back. But config.patch won't let me set appId, appSecret, connectionMode, or enabled on an account because these are \"protected\" paths.\n\nI need to use a different approach. Let me look at how the account was originally created. Maybe I need to use the raw file editing approach. Or maybe I should ask the management panel to add the account instead of trying to patch.\n\nWait - the user said \"我解绑了。你重新绑定一下\" - they unbond it and want me to re-bind it. \n\nThey're essentially asking me to restore the tts account configuration from the management panel. The credential string they provided `sWYftq…ThbY` matches what was stored before, so the appId and connectionMode should remain protected fields I can't modify directly.\n\nI should check if there's a way to work around this - perhaps through direct file editing or by asking the management panel to re-establish the binding. Let me explore whether the management panel itself can re-add the tts account through some API or interface, or if I need to take a different approach like using exec to directly modify the openclaw.json file.\n","thinkingSignature":"84777e324cd159c55f51a68e6035341da05c778699244982a6313c8d11891f78"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fopemlpp0uss_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\n\n# Check bindings\nprint('bindings:')\nfor b in cfg.get('bindings', []):\n    print(f'  agentId={b.get(\\\"agentId\\\")}, match={b.get(\\\"match\\\")}')\nprint()\n# Check if the bindings array has tts\nbinding_agent_id