{"type":"message","id":"f18e5fc3","parentId":"5c72dc0c","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:04:31.023Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, it's still showing \"sWYftq…ThbY\" instead of the actual secret. The masked value \"sWYftq…ThbY\" means the actual value was stored with a masking provider. Let me check the original raw file to see what the actual value was before it got masked.\n\nActually, looking at the raw content from the gateway.get output earlier, I saw the tts account had:\n```\n\"appSecret\": \"sWYftq…ThbY\"\n```\n\nThe user also provided the secret: `sWYftqexDF2zr6I36ofoyhSz8rLxThbY`\n\nBut when I write it, it gets converted to \"sWYftq…ThbY\" which means the system is masking it. This is because OpenClaw uses a secret provider that redacts the actual values when reading the config.\n\n\nI need to directly edit the raw JSON file instead of going through the config tool.\n","thinkingSignature":"30f4fac2eb8431766de5ad84a405ffe51f260f0f84e7a1a8465737cf490f3f50"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xsww5692l1w3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A5 '\"tts\"' /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json | head -10","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":284,"output":268,"cacheRead":100128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100680,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779541462492,"responseId":"0660d8d7940dbdea9ff4764aa0443a9b"}}
