{"type":"message","id":"866db316","parentId":"f6885611","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:13:26.800Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the problem clearly! Looking at the journalctl output:\n\n```\n5月 23 21:12:11 Halei node[521949]: 2026-05-23T21:12:11.750+08:00 [feishu] feishu[tts]: sender ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 not in DM allowlist\n```\n\nThe message at 21:12 was from `ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` - this is NOT the current user (ou_f590c429). This is the OLD user that had a session with tts. \n\nBut the current user's message (ou_f590c429) went to `feishu[default]` at 21:12:27, NOT to `feishu[tts]`:\n\n```\n5月 23 21:12:27 Halei node[521949]: 2026-05-23T21:12:27.192+08:00 [feishu] feishu[default]: received message from ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\n```\n\nThis confirms that when the user sends a message to the TK bot in Feishu, the message is being routed to `feishu[default]` instead of `feishu[tts]`!\n\nThe user's message at 21:12 went to `feishu[default]` with session `agent:main:feishu:default:direct:ou_f590c429`. This means the TK bot's Feishu app is NOT properly receiving the message - or it's being forwarded/redirected somewhere.\n\nWait - but the user said they sent a message to the TK bot in Feishu. \n\nThe TK bot's WebSocket connection for appId `cli_a930f78f51399bc6` is likely broken or not connecting at all, so when the user sends a DM to that appId, Feishu itself is routing the message to the default bot instead. The tts account is enabled and the binding exists, so the WebSocket for tts should be connecting - but something in Feishu's app configuration for that bot might be preventing proper message delivery.\n\nLooking at the session keys more carefully, the user's message is going to `agent:main:feishu:default:direct:ou_f590c429`, which means it's being routed to the kiit agent's default session, not to the tts agent. But I see tts has a session at `agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` from an old sender - so tts is receiving messages from that old sender, just not from the current user. The message is going to kiit instead because the routing logic is broken or the tts connection isn't working as expected. a different appId (like kiit's appId). Or maybe the user sent the message to the kiit app instead of the TK app?\n\nNo, the user confirmed they sent to TK's appId (cli_a930f78f51399bc6). The issue is likely that the TK app's WebSocket connection to Feishu is broken, so Feishu can't deliver messages to it. But the kiit app's WebSocket IS working, so messages go to kiit instead.\n\nOr wait - when you send a DM to a bot in Feishu, you need to open that bot's conversation specifically. The appId determines which bot. If TK's app isn't properly connected, Feishu might reject or redirect the message.\n\nActually, I think the real issue might be that when the user sent to TK's appId, Feishu sent it to OpenClaw via WebSocket, but OpenClaw routed it to the wrong account because of a session mismatch.\n\nThe bindings might not be working as expected. When a message arrives at `feishu[tts]` for a sender that doesn't have an active session, the system needs to check if there's a matching binding for `accountId=tts` and `channel=feishu`, then route to the tts agent. But if that binding isn't actually configured or isn't being evaluated first, the message could get routed elsewhere instead.\n\nLooking at the logs more carefully though - the user's message at 21:12:27 went to `feishu[default]`, not to `feishu[tts]`. So the TK app's WebSocket connection is probably receiving the message, but OpenClaw is routing it to the default account instead. This suggests the tts WebSocket might be failing silently while kiit's remains active, even though connectionMode is set to websocket globally.\n\nI should check whether tts actually established its WebSocket connection after the restart.\n","thinkingSignature":"74a961baaedebbc47f25b96b77d3ac4a9b23306eef8bf0908a2bdfb9d4203bb7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2nvc10kveblm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -n 200 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep -iE \"feishu\\[tts\\]|tts.*websocket|tts.*WebSocket|tts.*start|tts.*connect\" | tail -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2062,"output":1109,"cacheRead":103616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":106787,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779541998093,"responseId":"0660daee89a384a3b0b0e0bfdec2b165"}}
{"type":"message","id":"abdc6a67","parentId":"866db316","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:13:27.028Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2nvc10kveblm_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"5月 23 21:12:11 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[521949]: 2026-05-23T21:12:11.332+08:00 [feishu] feishu[tts]: message om_x100b6e2e37668ca4c25f82404f6e443 in chat oc_7cf732f57be08738470059baa24bd6d8 — immediate\n5月 23 21:12:11 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[521949]: 2026-05-23T21:12:11.745+08:00 [feishu] feishu[tts]: received message from ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 in oc_7cf732f57be08738470059baa24bd6d8 (p2p)\n5月 23 21:12:11 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[521949]: 2026-05-23T21:12:11.750+08:00 [feishu] feishu[tts]: sender ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 not in DM allowlist"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":52,"aggregated":"5月 23 21:12:11 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[521949]: 2026-05-23T21:12:11.332+08:00 [feishu] feishu[tts]: message om_x100b6e2e37668ca4c25f82404f6e443 in chat oc_7cf732f57be08738470059baa24bd6d8 — immediate\n5月 23 21:12:11 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[521949]: 2026-05-23T21:12:11.745+08:00 [feishu] feishu[tts]: received message from ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 in oc_7cf732f57be08738470059baa24bd6d8 (p2p)\n5月 23 21:12:11 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[521949]: 2026-05-23T21:12:11.750+08:00 [feishu] feishu[tts]: sender ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 not in DM allowlist","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779542007026}}
{"type":"message","id":"2f4344d6","parentId":"abdc6a67","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:13:35.391Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see a very important log line! At 21:12:11, the feishu[tts] account received a message from ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68. This is the OLD user that the tts session is for. But this message was rejected because \"sender ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 not in DM allowlist\".\n\nThe key problem: **The tts account's allowFrom does NOT include ou_f590c429 (the current user)!** \n\nWait, but earlier the tts account was supposed to inherit from global, and global allowFrom is ['ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb']. But now tts has an explicit account config, so it doesn't inherit anymore!\n\nLet me check what happened. When I added the tts account, I didn't set allowFrom on it. So now tts doesn't inherit the global allowFrom. I need to add allowFrom to the tts account.\n\nActually, let me look at the log again. At 21:12:11:\n- feishu[tts] received a message from ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\n- This is a DIFFERENT user (the old one), not ou_f590c429\n- The message was rejected: \"not in DM allowlist\"\n\nThis means:\n1. feishu[tts] IS receiving messages (WebSocket connection is working!)\n2. The allowFrom for tts only has ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 (the old user)\n\n\n3. ou_f590c429 (current user) is NOT in tts's allowFrom\n\nSo the tts account's WebSocket connection is actually working fine, but the current user isn't authorized because I never added them to the tts account's allowFrom list. I need to add ou_f590c429 to the tts account's allowFrom configuration.\n\nI can see the old session shows ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 was authorized, which is why they got through before. I should update the tts account to include both the old user and the new user in its allowFrom settings.","thinkingSignature":"88a2ab131d0f940b0f02c0fba9f94f9fa500e20cc56cd42d38907da741896050"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找到了！日志显示 **TK 的 WebSocket 连接是正常的**——它确实收到了消息，但被拒绝进入：\n\n```\nfeishu[tts]: sender ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 not in DM allowlist\n```\n\nTK 的 allowFrom 里只有旧用户 `ou_42b0f5aa...`，没有你的账号 `ou_f590c429`！\n\n我之前添加 tts 账号时漏掉了 allowFrom 配置。马上修复：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ly7bz5wzdvkn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\n\n# Add allowFrom and dmPolicy to tts account\ncfg['channels']['feishu']['accounts']['tts']['allowFrom'] = ['ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb']\ncfg['channels']['feishu']['accounts']['tts']['dmPolicy'] = 'allowlist'\n\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(cfg, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)\n\nprint('Fixed! tts account now has allowFrom and dmPolicy')\nprint('tts account:', json.dumps(cfg['channels']['feishu']['accounts']['tts'], indent=2))\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":394,"output":832,"cacheRead":105664,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":106890,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779542007363,"responseId":"0660daf7e5366a1f4db3f0d5a29a6b25"}}
