{"type":"message","id":"09a7a47b","parentId":"361d8098","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:13:40.690Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - now tts has its own allowFrom and dmPolicy. But wait - the appSecret is showing as masked (`sWYftq…ThbY`) in the output. This is because when I read the file with python3's json.load and then dump it back, the appSecret from lark-secrets provider is being masked/redacted.\n\nBut actually, the config schema showed that tts appSecret was stored with `\"source\": \"file\"` and `\"provider\": \"lark-secrets\"`. The actual appSecret value `sWYftqexDF2zr6I36ofoyhSz8rLxThbY` was stored in the file.\n\nWhen I loaded the JSON with python3 and saved it back, the masked value would have been written instead of the actual value. This means I've effectively lost the actual appSecret!\n\nWait, let me check the file content directly to see if the actual appSecret is still there.","thinkingSignature":"8eb6edc0cbfccd6851455931921bb13e3c9c6315747bd4bd33c549a75b57d8bb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ffa5gpe9zeps_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A3 '\"tts\"' /home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json | head -15","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":337,"output":252,"cacheRead":106048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":106637,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779542016003,"responseId":"0660db0006a26d0054b020fb1382d5a9"}}
