{"type":"message","id":"c3e97299","parentId":"697cf095","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:40:42.405Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user's message went to `kiit`, not `tts`. This confirms the issue: when the user sends a DM to the TK bot (cli_a930f78f51399bc6), the message is going to `kiit` instead of `tts`.This is a routing problem. The binding `agentId=tts, match={accountId=tts, channel=feishu}` should route messages to tts, but it seems like the routing is going to kiit instead.Wait - let me think about this again. The message comes in from Feishu with appId=cli_a930f78f51399bc6. OpenClaw needs to figure out which account this corresponds to. It looks up the appId in the accounts:- kiit has appId=cli_a93650c6fc785bce\n- tts has appId=cli_a930f78f51399bc6\n\nSo the appId should correctly identify the account as \"tts\". Then the binding `agentId=tts, match={accountId=tts, channel=feishu}` should route to the tts agent.But the user's message is going to kiit! This means either:\n1. The appId lookup is returning kiit instead of tts2. The routing logic is bypassing the binding and using a different mechanism\n3. There's something wrong with how the Feishu plugin is routing this particular message\n\nActually wait - I just realized something. The user's message metadata shows this conversation is \"direct\" with the user (ou_f590c429). But the message_id in the current conversation is `om_x100b6e2e998b3938c2539f6735a6d4b`. And the journalctl shows the user sent a message at 21:36:53 to kiit.\n\nThe user said they tried sending a message to TK in Feishu and it didn't work. \n\nWhen they send to TK, the message is going to kiit. That's the problem. Looking back at the binding configuration, I need to verify whether the account mapping is actually working correctly. The binding has `agentId: \"tts\"` and `match: {accountId: \"tts\", channel: \"feishu\"}`, but the routing might not be checking the accountId in the way I expected. Let me reconsider how the Feishu plugin determines which account receives a message based on its appId, and whether there's a mismatch between the account resolution and the binding lookup.\n\nI should check the gateway logs to see what appId was actually received and which account was matched for this message, since that would reveal if there's a resolution issue or if the binding logic isn't working as intended.\n","thinkingSignature":"02153eea972743f9d883a5bb8b5769c99960d0d2cfc157759f948ebf86b4aebf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h2nrh4g4xoja_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -n 2000 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep -iE \"appId.*cli_a930|cli_a930.*appId|account.*tts|tts.*account|routing\" | tail -30","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":456,"output":647,"cacheRead":108303,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109406,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779543623217,"responseId":"0660e1474f3bf862e1af2bce235f271b"}}
