{"type":"message","id":"841e488d","parentId":"b26b6c2e","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:43:25.980Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue now! The journalctl only shows the tts receiving messages from `ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` (not ou_f590c429). And there's NO log of tts receiving messages from ou_f590c429.\n\nThis means either:\n1. The user's messages to TK are NOT reaching the feishu[tts] WebSocket at all\n2. The feishu[tts] WebSocket is NOT connected/receiving events since the last restart\n\nThe fact that the last restart (21:36 timeframe) shows tts receiving messages from ou_42b0f5aa suggests tts IS connected. But it's only receiving from ou_42b0f5aa, NOT from ou_f590c429.\n\nWait - but the user's message at 21:36 went to kiit (feishu[kiit]), not tts. The user is messaging kiit right now (this conversation). But when they try TK in Feishu, TK doesn't respond.\n\nLet me check what happens when the user sends a message to TK. If the user sends to TK (appId: cli_a930f78f51399bc6), Feishu routes it to OpenClaw. OpenClaw should recognize the appId as tts account.\n\nActually, maybe I need to verify which appId the user is actually sending to when they \"send to TK\". The user confirmed the app_id is `cli_a930f78f51399bc6` for TK. But maybe the user is actually sending to a different app?\n\nActually wait - let me look at the Feishu app architecture. When a user opens a DM with a bot in Feishu, the message goes to that bot's appId. So if the user opens TK's bot page (appId: cli_a930f78f51399bc6), messages should go to that appId.\n\nBut I don't see any log of feishu[tts] receiving from ou_f590c429. \n\nThe message might be going to TK's appId but Feishu isn't delivering it to our WebSocket. Or the feishu[tts] WebSocket stopped receiving events after the restart. Actually, I need to reconsider how the routing works - when a user sends a message to the TK bot in Feishu, Feishu should send it to the webhook endpoint with the app_id parameter, which our gateway uses to route to the correct account.\n\nBut our gateway uses WebSocket mode, so Feishu sends events through the persistent WebSocket connection. The WebSocket connection is established for each account using the app credentials. Since both accounts use websocket mode, they should both be getting events. But only kiit shows in the logs receiving messages from ou_f590c429, not tts.\n\nLet me look at the routing logic more carefully. When the user sends a message to TK (cli_a930f78f51399bc6), Feishu delivers it to the app's webhook URL. In WebSocket mode, Feishu sends events through the persistent WebSocket connection. The gateway identifies which account based on the app_id in the event payload. It should map cli_a930f78f51399bc6 to the tts account.\n\nBut I don't see tts receiving any events from ou_f590c429. There might be two separate issues here. First, the binding was wrong (TK was bound to main instead of tts), which we fixed. Second, after the restart, tts isn't showing up in the logs at all for receiving events from ou_f590c429. This could mean either the user's messages to TK aren't actually reaching our gateway, or the feishu[tts] WebSocket is connected but not receiving events for this user.\n\nWait - I just noticed something. The message at 21:36 went to kiit, and I'm responding to the user right now in kiit. So the user is messaging kiit in this conversation. But the user also said \"不行\" which suggests they're also trying TK separately. The issue is that there's no log showing feishu[tts] receiving anything from ou_f590c429. Either TK's events aren't reaching our gateway, or the feishu[tts] WebSocket stopped processing after the restart.\n\nMaybe I should check if the user actually sent to TK and whether it appeared in the logs. The real problem might be that feishu[tts]'s WebSocket is broken - it was connected before the restart but now it's not processing events anymore. I should try restarting again or check the connection more carefully.\n\nActually, the user said \"不行\" which means they're still not getting responses. But I am responding to them right now through kiit. So the user is telling me that TK (tts) isn't working, not kiit. The issue is that TK's WebSocket isn't properly receiving messages from Feishu for the user.\n\nLet me look at the binding configuration again. The binding routes `accountId=tts, channel=feishu` to `agentId=tts`. When a message comes in on feishu with accountId=tts, it should go to the tts agent. But earlier the gateway config showed a bindings list that included main, kiit, tts, and others - so the routing should work. But maybe there's something wrong with how the feishu account is being matched to the binding.\n\nWait - the user unbinded the TK bot from the third-party panel and asked me to rebind it. So the TK bot was previously bound to main (kiit), which is why messages to TK were going to kiit. I need to check what the current binding looks like and whether TK is now properly bound to tts so messages route correctly.\n","thinkingSignature":"f06b258c6dd1546192891d46f0f2f7ae2976eaa0db857a4f832c521985b0d864"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xcazbsoh3dcl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -n 100 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | tail -50","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":179,"output":1253,"cacheRead":109703,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111135,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779543750403,"responseId":"0660e1c67b88e1cbbb4ec9641df0ac15"}}
