{"type":"message","id":"c608720b","parentId":"91cf1f82","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:43:53.184Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problem is very clear now. The user's message at 21:36 was received by `feishu[kiit]`, NOT by `feishu[tts]`. The message went to the wrong account.\n\nThis means the routing is still wrong. When the user sends a DM to the TK bot (appId: cli_a930f78f51399bc6), it's being routed to kiit instead of tts.\n\nThe issue might be:\n1. The binding isn't being used properly\n2. The message is being sent to kiit's appId, not tts's appId\n\nWait - the user is saying they sent a message to TK and it didn't work. But the journal shows the message going to feishu[kiit]. This could mean:\n1. The user actually sent the message to kiit (wrong bot), not TK\n2. OR the routing from Feishu to OpenClaw is wrong\n\nLet me think about the architecture:\n- User in Feishu opens a DM with TK bot (appId: cli_a930f78f51399bc6)\n- Feishu delivers the message to OpenClaw via WebSocket\n- The WebSocket message contains the appId (so OpenClaw knows which bot/app received the message)\n- OpenClaw should look at the appId, map it to account \"tts\", then look at bindings to route to agent \"tts\"\n\nBut the journal shows the message going to feishu[kiit]. This means either:\n1. Feishu delivered it to the wrong app (kiit instead of tts)\n2. OR the appId in the WebSocket message is kiit's appId, not tts's appId\n\nWait - the user said they sent the message to TK. But maybe they actually opened the kiit conversation, not the TK conversation? The user confirmed earlier that the app_id shown in the TK bot info was correct (cli_a930f78f51399bc6). But maybe the user was looking at the wrong info.\n\nActually, let me re-examine the issue. Looking at the bindings:\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"route\",\n  \"agentId\": \"main\",\n  \"match\": {\n    \"accountId\": \"kiit\",\n    \"channel\": \"feishu\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe binding maps `accountId: kiit` to `agentId: main`. But the tts account has accountId \"tts\", which should map to agentId \"tts\". So the binding itself seems correct. The issue must be that when the message arrives, it's being attributed to the wrong account - it's arriving as kiit instead of tts.\n\nThis suggests either the user messaged the kiit bot instead of tts, or Feishu is delivering the message to the wrong bot's endpoint. Looking at the feishu[kiit] logs, the sender ou_f590c429 is correct, but the message came through kiit's WebSocket rather than tts's. This could mean the user opened the kiit conversation in Feishu by mistake, or the message was routed incorrectly at the Feishu level.\n\nThe `defaultAccount: kiit` setting might be intercepting tts messages if there's a fallback logic issue. I'm wondering if the problem is that the user's message is actually reaching the kiit bot session (which would explain why I'm responding), or if the binding configuration for routing tts messages to the tts agent isn't being applied correctly.\n\nThe user confirmed the app_id for TK is correct, so they're definitely messaging the right bot. The issue must be on the OpenClaw side - either the feishu[tts] WebSocket is receiving the message but the routing to the tts agent is broken, or the message isn't reaching feishu[tts] at all. Since the user is getting a response in this conversation but TK isn't responding independently, the most likely explanation is that the message is being routed to kiit instead of tts, or the feishu[tts] channel isn't properly delivering messages to the tts agent session.\n\nLet me try sending a test message to the tts agent to see if it actually receives anything. The user might be testing from the wrong conversation or there could be a session routing issue causing the message to go to kiit instead.\n\nThe core problem seems to be that tts isn't creating new sessions when messages arrive, even though the allowlist and policy should allow it. I should verify whether the feishu[tts] WebSocket connection itself is functioning properly, or if there's a deeper routing or session management issue preventing the bot from responding independently.\n","thinkingSignature":"e47390d4a1ecc8c04510ca6929a15555256a547966b811e0a460411e1ed391b1"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n我看到问题了——你的消息被路由到了 kiit，而不是 tts。而且 tts 的 WebSocket 在重启后没有输出连接日志。\n\n让我彻底排查一下。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6hwebccp61ez_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -n 5000 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"21:36|21:37|21:38|21:39\" | grep -iE \"feishu|account|route|tts|kiit\" | head -30","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1992,"output":1087,"cacheRead":109879,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112958,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779543806627,"responseId":"0660e1ffe1c7069144f5c18cecaa5891"}}
