1:24:40.028+08:00 [feishu] feishu[agent-orchestrator]: bot open_id resolved: ou_8efa215242ce15529fb580084ebbb16b\n5月 23 21:24:40 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[522187]: 2026-05-23T21:24:40.030+08:00 [feishu] feishu[default]: bot open_id resolved: ou_11f95142ee4622f42acc029c870f68bb\n5月 23 21:24:40 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[522187]: 2026-05-23T21:24:40.031+08:00 [feishu] feishu[content]: bot open_id resolved: ou_4352abe17dbd0341b0b4862bbce52cc8\n5月 23 21:24:40 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[522187]: 2026-05-23T21:24:40.033+08:00 [feishu] feishu[traffic]: bot open_id resolved: ou_2de0ac5c4a77f6a9122fed2cacd6d2b5\n5月 23 21:24:40 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[522187]: 2026-05-23T21:24:40.034+08:00 [feishu] feishu[ops]: bot open_id resolved: ou_1f60239e12d538056c0cd6fe46ec0df1\n5月 23 21:24:40 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[522187]: 2026-05-23T21:24:40.036+08:00 [feishu] feishu[director]: bot open_id resolved: ou_2c508959e24aa02c519322b23e6c3f9d\n5月 23 21:24:40 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[522187]: 2026-05-23T21:24:40.037+08:00 [feishu] feishu[finance]: bot open_id resolved: ou_e1da3237fc1c0150c845c6102897907c\n5月 23 21:24:40 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[522187]: 2026-05-23T21:24:40.038+08:00 [feishu] feishu[review]: bot open_id resolved: ou_a6e217eff510ab163338682d9e6db70c\n5月 23 21:24:40 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[522187]: 2026-05-23T21:24:40.040+08:00 [feishu] feishu[koc]: bot open_id resolved: ou_516c5ca5fa836a3af31e285d707b459f\n5月 23 21:24:40 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[522187]: 2026-05-23T21:24:40.041+08:00 [feishu] feishu[tts]: bot open_id resolved: ou_09c92e096986a0fcd5b389561a0a1a84","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779543982187}}
{"type":"message","id":"75926922","parentId":"52b19db5","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:46:41.135Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see at 21:24:40 (after the restart at 21:24), feishu[tts] started and resolved its bot open_id as ou_09c92e096986a0fcd5b389561a0a1a84. And feishu[kiit] also started.\n\nSo both tts and kiit WebSockets were established at restart.\n\nThen at 21:36:53, the user's message (om_x100b6e2e998b3938c2539f6735a6d4b) went to kiit, not tts.\n\nThe issue is that the user is sending messages to TK's app_id (cli_a930f78f51399bc6), but somehow the message is being routed to kiit instead of tts.\n\nWait - let me look at the routing more carefully. When the user sends a DM to TK in Feishu:\n1. Feishu receives the message and routes it to the app (TK's app_id: cli_a930f78f51399bc6)\n2. OpenClaw receives the message via the WebSocket for the TK bot\n3. OpenClaw needs to determine which account to attribute this message to\n\nActually, wait. The WebSocket connection is per-app. When the user sends a DM to TK, Feishu delivers it through the WebSocket connection that TK's app (cli_a930f78f51399bc6) has open.\n\nSo OpenClaw should receive the message and attribute it to the tts account (since it's from TK's app_id).\n\nBut the journal shows the message going to feishu[kiit], not feishu[tts].\n\nThis is very strange. The message should go to feishu[tts] since the sender is sending to TK's app_id.\n\nUnless... the message IS going to feishu[tts] but then something is happening that routes it to kiit? That doesn't make sense.\n\nOR... maybe the user's message to TK is actually being delivered to kiit's WebSocket somehow? Maybe Feishu has some kind of routing issue where the same user sending messages to different bots sometimes gets mixed up?\n\n\nActually, I think the problem is simpler: when the user sends a message to TK (app_id cli_a930f78f51399bc6), Feishu delivers it to the correct WebSocket for that app, but OpenClaw is somehow routing it to the wrong account. The journal clearly shows kiit receiving the message, which means the feishu plugin is attributing it to kiit instead of tts. This suggests there might be an issue with how the app_id is being matched to the account in OpenClaw's configuration.\n\nLet me look at the actual config file to verify what I wrote is being used. I'm wondering if the config.patch command is using the full unmasked appSecret value or if there's a redacted version being used instead.\n","thinkingSignature":"52f161d650cf456d663c3a265bd198a8e795cfc9263a7bf83a7657dae70bef21"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t6r1zb40di6w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\naccounts = cfg['channels']['feishu']['accounts']\nprint('All accounts:', list(accounts.keys()))\nprint()\nfor name, acc in accounts.items():\n    print(f'{name}: appId={acc.get(\\\"appId\\\")}, allowFrom={acc.get(\\\"allowFrom\\\")}, dmPolicy={acc.get(\\\"dmPolicy\\\")}')\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":862,"output":751,"cacheRead":113595,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115208,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779543982614,"responseId":"0660e2b09c712124eb1f234aad325993"}}
