{"type":"message","id":"a926f7c0","parentId":"851c63ce","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:51:27.776Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so after the restart, there's still no tts feishu session for ou_f590c429. The tts only has a webchat session.\n\nThe key question is: why does the user message to tts bot not create a feishu session for tts?\n\nThe user's messages at 21:36 were routed to kiit. Let me think about this...\n\nThe feishu[default] account doesn't have appId set. But it has dmPolicy=pairing. And the global defaultAccount is \"kiit\".\n\nBut the bindings say route to tts when accountId=tts. So when the user messages the tts bot (appId=cli_a930f78f51399bc6), it should match the binding for tts (accountId=tts).\n \nI see it now - the tts account has allowFrom set to ou_f590c429, which means that user's message should be accepted by the tts channel. The routing should work since the tts binding matches when feishu[tts] receives a message from that user. But why isn't a session being created?\n\nThe session storage shows no feishu direct session for ou_f590c429 with tts - only kiit has that. Maybe the issue is that messages from ou_f590c429 aren't actually reaching feishu[tts] at all, or the message flow is getting interrupted somewhere.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the user only has one Feishu account, so when they message the TK bot, it goes through the official Feishu app on that account. The TK bot's app_id (cli_a930f78f51399bc6) is what identifies it to Feishu's servers, but the routing seems to be sending the message to kiit instead - possibly because the default account in the configuration is taking precedence or the bindings aren't being evaluated correctly for incoming messages from this particular user. The tts account successfully initialized its WebSocket connection to the TK bot, so the bot is properly registered with Feishu's servers. But the \"sender not in DM allowlist\" error appearing in the logs suggests the allowFrom configuration isn't being checked correctly—the system should only block messages from the specific users in that list, but it seems to be rejecting the sender regardless.\n\nLooking at the actual messages in the log, both ou_f590c429 and ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 are being processed through feishu[kiit], which means messages to the TK bot are being routed to the wrong account entirely. The appId cli_a930f78f51399bc6 should route to tts based on the bindings, but something in the routing logic is sending it to kiit instead—possibly the binding condition isn't matching correctly or the routing priority is off.\n\nWhen a user sends a message to the TK bot, Feishu delivers it to the app's configured webhook endpoint. The feishu plugin is responsible for parsing which account should handle it, so if the TK app_id isn't mapping to the tts account, the plugin likely isn't parsing the app_id from the message payload correctly, or it's defaulting to the main agent when it should be routing to tts.\n\nLet me verify what app_id the TK bot is actually configured with and whether kiit's allowFrom is actually set to None or if it's inheriting from elsewhere. The WebSocket mode should receive messages directly, but the routing isn't matching the accountId to the tts agent. Let me check if there's a recent feishu session in kiit's directory to see what's actually happening with the message routing.\n\nI'm seeing the issue now—the user ou_f590c429 is sending messages to the TK bot's conversation, but the routing is going to feishu[kiit] instead of feishu[tts], which is why they're getting a response from KIIT rather than the expected bot.\n\nThe problem is that when messages arrive from TK's Feishu bot account, the system doesn't recognize they should go to the tts agent. I need to check how the default account is set and which account should actually be handling these incoming messages from TK's bot.\n","thinkingSignature":"54a889c6aa96b1bb85a6abace660ff281a0feef55b8cc7313054e770ed38ba0f"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n关键发现：用户消息进了 kiit 而不是 tts。让我确认一下 routing 的问题。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_18p3fby5syy0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\nfeishu = cfg['channels']['feishu']\nprint('defaultAccount:', feishu.get('defaultAccount'))\nprint('global allowFrom:', feishu.get('allowFrom'))\nprint('global dmPolicy:', feishu.get('dmPolicy'))\nprint()\nprint('kiit account:')\nkiit = feishu['accounts']['kiit']\nprint('  allowFrom:', kiit.get('allowFrom'))\nprint('  dmPolicy:', kiit.get('dmPolicy'))\nprint()\nprint('tts account:')\ntts = feishu['accounts']['tts']\nprint('  allowFrom:', tts.get('allowFrom'))\nprint('  dmPolicy:', tts.get('dmPolicy'))\n\"","timeout":5}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_18p3fby5syy0_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -n 5000 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep \"feishu\\[tts\\]\" | head -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":280,"output":1151,"cacheRead":66688,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68119,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779544277402,"responseId":"0660e3d5e6c4f6805deec20fe5900e9a"}}
