{"type":"message","id":"0d87d8a7","parentId":"2ed34c12","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:54:49.941Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue clearly!\n\n21:48:51 - session is stalled (age=693s)\n21:49:18 - kiit dispatches (replies=1) but session is still stuck\n21:49:18 - kiit receives another message and dispatches (but session already stuck)\n21:49:56 - the user's new message (om_x100b6e2f46f7ccacc4e9569044a24c8) is QUEUED because session is stalled\n21:53:22 - session still processing, still queued (age=148s from... wait, 21:49:56 to 21:53:22 is about 206 seconds)\n\n\n21:53:57 - finally dispatch complete with replies=2\n\nSo the user's 21:49 message got queued at 21:49:56, then waited in that queue until 21:53:57 while the session was blocked on a model call that had been running since 21:48:51. The session had been processing for 693 seconds before the message was even queued at 21:49:56.\n\nThe queue depth stayed at 1 because that new message had to wait behind the active work, and it only took about 4 minutes to finally complete. The issue is that kiit's session is backed up with queued messages, which means kiit isn't responding to the user in a timely manner—it processed the user's message but the user never received the reply.\n\nLooking at the timeline more carefully, the user sent a message at 21:49, it got queued at 21:49:56 due to the stalled session, and only completed at 21:53:57. The fact that kiit was actively processing something during this window suggests the real problem is that kiit is so backed up with queued requests that it can't keep up with new messages, which would also explain why tts isn't getting any messages at all. The session stalled at 21:48:51 with an active model call that was already 129 seconds old. When kiit received messages at 21:49:18, it processed them despite the stalled session being reported—a \"stalled\" classification triggers recovery attempts but doesn't prevent dispatch. The actual issue is the long-running session itself: a model call is blocking new messages from being processed properly.\n\nLooking at the diagnostic data, the age of 693 seconds (about 11.5 minutes) combined with the queue depth of 1 and the fact that new messages keep coming in suggests kiit's session is being overwhelmed by a backlog of requests. The user is likely sending messages to kiit because it appears as the default bot, but those messages are getting queued while kiit is still processing previous work.\n\nNow I'm realizing the core issue: messages to TK are going to kiit instead because feishu is routing based on the app, and messages to the main Kiit bot (cli_a93650c6fc785bce) are what the user is actually sending. The question is whether this routing is happening at the feishu platform level or through some other mechanism.\n\nLooking at the dispatch logs, when messages arrive at feishu[kiit], they're being routed to the main agent session instead of the feishu-specific session. But the feishu session that was created at the beginning has an active model call running and messages are queued behind it—this suggests the issue is within the kiit agent itself, where the feishu session is being handled by a different agent than expected. The long-running session that started around 21:48:51 is consuming the model, and the queued messages at 21:49:56 are waiting for it to finish—likely processing a complex task. Looking at the timeline, this session kicked off around 21:36 and is still going, and messages to both kiit and the TK bot are being queued because the main agent is stuck processing something and can't handle new requests. I see the issue now—the kiit agent is stuck processing something that's tying up the model, which is why messages to kiit aren't getting replies and messages to the TK bot are also queued up behind this blockage. The problem isn't that the TK bot itself is broken, it's that the kiit agent has a long-running session that's consuming all available processing capacity, so new messages can't get through. The dispatch logs show both messages were sent through feishu[kiit], but the user is reporting that messages to the TK bot still aren't getting replies, which suggests the TK bot is also blocked by the same queue issue. The core problem is that kiit has queued messages (timestamp 1779541800000 is 21:50) and a long-running session still processing. I need to find a way to recover or reset kiit's session to clear this backlog. I should focus on fixing the kiit session issue first since that's where the actual bottleneck is. The kiit session is stuck with a queued message, and that's why kiit isn't responding. Let me figure out what command or action can interrupt this long-running session.\n","thinkingSignature":"bd3110e7b917477c515c6768cd5c55c61b618d16eaf6542cbb6bf62bd0d88185"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xfze5f17mz91_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -n 500 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep \"stalled session\\|long-running session\\|dispatching.*agent\\|activeWorkKind\" | tail -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1068,"output":1114,"cacheRead":76800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78982,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779544479713,"responseId":"0660e4a05972a8958a900259356b4979"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f606b948","parentId":"0d87d8a7","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:54:50.353Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xfze5f17mz91_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"5月 23 21:48:51 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[523018]: 2026-05-23T21:48:51.082+08:00 [diagnostic] stalled session: sessionId=405b68a9-c988-46c4-9527-0873f7b2008e sessionKey=agent:main:feishu:kiit:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb state=processing age=693s queueDepth=1 reason=active_work_without_progress classification=stalled_agent_run activeWorkKind=model_call lastProgress=model_call:started lastProgressAge=129s recovery=none\n5月 23 21:49:18 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[523018]: 2026-05-23T21:49:18.771+08:00 [feishu] feishu[kiit]: dispatching to agent (session=agent:main:main)\n5月 23 21:53:22 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[523018]: 2026-05-23T21:53:22.863+08:00 [diagnostic] long-running session: sessionId=405b68a9-c988-46c4-9527-0873f7b2008e sessionKey=agent:main:feishu:kiit:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb state=processing age=148s queueDepth=1 reason=queued_behind_active_work classification=long_running activeWorkKind=model_call lastProgress=model_call:started lastProgressAge=0s recovery=none\n5月 23 21:53:57 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[523018]: 2026-05-23T21:53:57.842+08:00 [feishu] feishu[kiit]: dispatching to agent (session=agent:main:main)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":139,"aggregated":"5月 23 21:48:51 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[523018]: 2026-05-23T21:48:51.082+08:00 [diagnostic] stalled session: sessionId=405b68a9-c988-46c4-9527-0873f7b2008e sessionKey=agent:main:feishu:kiit:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb state=processing age=693s queueDepth=1 reason=active_work_without_progress classification=stalled_agent_run activeWorkKind=model_call lastProgress=model_call:started lastProgressAge=129s recovery=none\n5月 23 21:49:18 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[523018]: 2026-05-23T21:49:18.771+08:00 [feishu] feishu[kiit]