{"type":"message","id":"17add377","parentId":"389ef3ea","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:55:49.297Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user completed the Feishu authorization. But this metadata is a bit confusing - it's showing \"auth-complete\" for message_id, which suggests this is the authorization confirmation message. The sender is ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb.\n\nBut wait - this message is coming through the current session (kiit/main), not through any specific bot. The message_id format \"om_x100b6e2e96c4d8a0c3464c9eebd097b:auth-complete\" is unusual.\n\nActually, looking at the conversation context - this is the current conversation with KIIT (the main session through Feishu). \n\nSo this is KIIT receiving the authorization completion message directly from Feishu, which means the authorization flow worked and the user has granted the necessary permissions.\n\nNow I need to check if the tts account can actually receive messages from the user's open_id - that's the critical test here since the user said TK wasn't responding before.\n","thinkingSignature":"bbae89a07565ff0bbcaca393ee2465df9d127d24ffa9ac114813d3dc91f92d89"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xusvimn4le0a_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sleep 3 && journalctl -n 50 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"21:5[4-9]|22:\" | grep -iE \"feishu\\[tts\\]|feishu\\[kiit\\]|tts.*dispatch\" | tail -20","timeout":8}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5282,"output":307,"cacheRead":75456,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81045,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779544542220,"responseId":"0660e4de1bca674f5e35f165c3f7dff8"}}
