{"type":"message","id":"decd818c","parentId":"5a9cf973","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:56:03.047Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The auth-complete message came in. And I can see that kiit is processing it - \"dispatch complete (queuedFinal=true, replies=1)\". But wait - I just restarted the gateway (SIGUSR1), but the pid is still 523018, which is the old gateway process. And the logs show 21:55, so the gateway hasn't restarted yet or the old process is still running.\n\nActually, the gateway restart takes time. The SIGUSR1 was sent to the old process, and a new one should be starting. But the logs show the old process (523018) is still running at 21:55.\n\nWait, actually - the gateway restart with SIGUSR1 is a hot reload, not a full restart. \n\nIt reloads the config but keeps running. So the gateway is still pid 523018. The feishu_im_user_message result shows an auth-complete message from the user completing the OAuth flow. Looking at the dispatch complete logs from 21:55, the user's message at 21:49 (om_x100b6e2e96c4d8a0c3464c9eebd097b) got a reply from kiit at 21:55 - 6 minutes later. That's really slow response time.\n\nBut the user saying \"不行\" might mean kiit replied but the reply was wrong, or the reply didn't go through for some reason. I need to check what that reply actually was.\n","thinkingSignature":"65df97099d63dc282bb1a90df035646309d21265beb693add23cd8e9358d23dc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_prsi770xqzp9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -n 100 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"21:5[0-9]|22:\" | grep -iE \"dispatch|reply|content|feishu\\[tts\\]|tts.*message\" | tail -20","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":380,"output":395,"cacheRead":80704,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81479,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779544552825,"responseId":"0660e4e965bf