{"type":"message","id":"21ccba6f","parentId":"decd818c","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:56:03.278Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_prsi770xqzp9_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"5月 23 21:55:15 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[523018]: 2026-05-23T21:55:15.537+08:00 [reload] config change requires channel reload (feishu) — deferring until 2 operation(s), 3 reply(ies), 1 embedded run(s) complete\n5月 23 21:55:37 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[523018]: 2026-05-23T21:55:37.963+08:00 [feishu] feishu[kiit]: dispatch complete (queuedFinal=true, replies=1)\n5月 23 21:55:45 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[523018]: 2026-05-23T21:55:45.990+08:00 [reload] channel reload still deferred after 30449ms with 2 operation(s), 4 reply(ies), 1 embedded run(s) active"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":52,"aggregated":"5月 23 21:55:15 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[523018]: 2026-05-23T21:55:15.537+08:00 [reload] config change requires channel reload (feishu) — deferring until 2 operation(s), 3 reply(ies), 1 embedded run(s) complete\n5月 23 21:55:37 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[523018]: 2026-05-23T21:55:37.963+08:00 [feishu] feishu[kiit]: dispatch complete (queuedFinal=true, replies=1)\n5月 23 21:55:45 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[523018]: 2026-05-23T21:55:45.990+08:00 [reload] channel reload still deferred after 30449ms with 2 operation(s), 4 reply(ies), 1 embedded run(s) active","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779544563266}}
{"type":"message","id":"e2f6ebbc","parentId":"21ccba6f","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:56:12.759Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the problem now! The config change requires a channel reload (feishu), but the reload is being deferred because there are still active operations, replies, and embedded runs. The reload has been deferred for 30+ seconds. This means the tts config change hasn't been applied yet!\n\nLet me check if there's a way to force the reload. Or maybe I need to wait for the active operations to complete before the reload can happen.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully:\n- 21:55:15: config change requires channel reload but is deferred\n- 21:55:45: still deferred after 30449ms with 2 operations, 4 replies, 1 embedded run\n\n\n- The kiit session (405b68a9) is the main blocker—it's been active since before 21:55 and is blocking the channel reload for feishu, which means the tts config changes won't take effect until that session completes and the reload can finally execute.\n\nI could potentially kill that session to unblock the reload, but the user is actually getting replies from kiit right now, so I need to be careful not to disrupt an active conversation. Let me check what else is in the queue to see if there's another way forward.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the user confirmed they completed the Feishu authorization, and looking at the metadata around the TK bot messages, those were sent before the authorization happened. Now that authorization is complete, the kiit replies should be coming through properly—the dispatch logs show \"replies=1\" which confirms kiit is responding.\n\nSo the real issue is that kiit's session has been continuously processing for about 30 minutes, and new messages are just getting queued behind that active work. The gateway reload is deferred because of this long-running session, which means the tts config changes haven't actually been applied yet. I need to either let the current processing complete naturally or find a way to clear the queue so the new config can take effect.\n\nBut wait—the user is saying they're not getting replies at all, which is different from getting delayed replies. Looking at the dispatch logs more carefully, \"replies=1\" and \"replies=2\" probably just mean kiit sent acknowledgment messages back to Feishu, not necessarily the actual response content. The session is stuck in processing mode, so the actual reply might be failing to generate or send back.\n\nLet me focus on the TK problem first though. The user sent a message to TK at 21:55 and is waiting for a response.\n\nThe real issue is that the feishu config reload is blocked by the active long-running session. I need to either restart the gateway or find another way to clear that stuck session so the new config can take effect and TK can start processing messages.\n\nLooking at the timeline more carefully—the authorization completed at 21:55, the config reload was triggered then, but it's been deferred because kiit's session has been running for over 30 minutes. The question is whether kiit actually processed the authorization message before getting stuck, or if that message also got queued behind the existing workload.\n\nThe metadata message_id `om_x100b6e2e96c4d8a0c3464c9eebd097b` suggests this is an authorization confirmation tied to the Feishu OAuth flow the user just completed. The kiit replies=2 response likely included the auth confirmation card, but the user may not have seen it if they're not looking at that chat thread.\n\nNow I'm thinking about what actually matters for the user right now: whether TK is configured correctly to receive messages once the gateway reloads.\n\nThe issue is that the feishu channel reload is blocked by the active kiit session, so I should restart the gateway to force the reload. But I need to be careful—if kiit is actively processing a message and I restart, that work gets lost. Let me check what kiit's current status is before deciding whether to force the restart.\n\nThe session is over 30 minutes old with \"activeWorkKind=model_call:started\" and \"queueDepth=1\", which means it's waiting on a model response. This could be a genuine slow operation or something stuck. Either way, forcing a restart would abandon that work. But the config reload is critical for TK to function properly, so I need to weigh the tradeoff here.\n\nActually, I think the right move is to restart the gateway and let kiit's session recover naturally when it times out. The user can always resend their message if needed. Let me trigger the restart now.\n","thinkingSignature":"d7b2c1472d194db649e010a5ab31a00a39f980eda92a36137d066191919a5590"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oe8djkyqfl0w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -n 100 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"feishu\\[tts\\]|tts.*WebSocket\" | tail -10","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":347,"output":1004,"cacheRead":81056,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82407,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779544563516,"responseId":"0660e4f3fb8e10a6fa269b721563d622"}}
