at step CHDIR spawning /home/halei/.n/bin/node: No such file or directory\n5月 23 21:56:32 halei-Surface-Pro-4 systemd[843]: openclaw-admin.service: Main process exited, code=exited, status=200/CHDIR\n5月 23 21:56:32 halei-Surface-Pro-4 systemd[843]: openclaw-admin.service: Failed with result 'exit-code'.\n5月 23 21:56:38 halei-Surface-Pro-4 systemd[843]: openclaw-admin.service: Scheduled restart job, restart counter is at 54871.\n5月 23 21:56:38 halei-Surface-Pro-4 systemd[843]: Stopped OpenClaw Admin Panel (port 3001).\n5月 23 21:56:38 halei-Surface-Pro-4 systemd[843]: Started OpenClaw Admin Panel (port 3001).\n5月 23 21:56:38 halei-Surface-Pro-4 node[525003]: openclaw-admin.service: Changing to the requested working directory failed: No such file or directory\n5月 23 21:56:38 halei-Surface-Pro-4 systemd[525003]: openclaw-admin.service: Failed at step CHDIR spawning /home/halei/.n/bin/node: No such file or directory\n5月 23 21:56:38 halei-Surface-Pro-4 systemd[843]: openclaw-admin.service: Main process exited, code=exited, status=200/CHDIR\n5月 23 21:56:38 halei-Surface-Pro-4 systemd[843]: openclaw-admin.service: Failed with result 'exit-code'.","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779544598891}}
{"type":"message","id":"b6c62342","parentId":"9ed81ccf","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:56:51.428Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue now! The last line shows:\n\n```\n[feishu] feishu[tts]: sender ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 not paired, creating pairing request\n```\n\nThe tts bot is now in `pairing` mode - it's asking the sender to pair! But wait, this is sender `ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68`, NOT the user's sender ID `ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb`. \n\nSo the issue with tts having dmPolicy=pairing is that it asks EVERY sender to pair, not just the user. \n\nThe user's ID would still be checked against the pairing list since it's not paired yet, so the real problem is that dmPolicy=pairing forces a pairing flow that never completes. I need to switch tts back to dmPolicy=allowlist so it inherits the global allowFrom setting which already has the user's ID. But the channel reload is still deferred with active operations, so I'll need to wait for that to complete before making the change. The reload is blocked because the main agent has long-running operations (21:55 logs show dispatch complete with replies pending). The kiit session is blocked on model_call. This long-running session is preventing the channel reload. I should wait for this session to complete, or try to cancel it. Actually, looking at the session ID `405b68a9-c988-46c4-9527-0873f7b2008e` — this has been running since around 21:37-21:39. The user sent messages and kiit tried to respond but the model call is stuck.\n\nI think the kiit session is stuck because it's waiting for the model (minimax) to respond, which might be failing. This is blocking all channel reloads. I should either kill this session or wait for it to timeout.\n\nBut first, let me fix the tts dmPolicy issue. I'll use Python to directly edit the JSON file since the config.patch can't handle nested feishu account fields.\n","thinkingSignature":"f71f3c0edadcce02583d78a1b7d931928058a479cad2070241ac496b32ae032a"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找到了！tts 刚收到一条消息，但用的是 `pairing` 模式——它在等 pairing 确认，不是 allowlist。需要改回 allowlist。kiit 的 model_call 卡住了，正在阻塞 channel reload。让我同时处理这两个问题。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gjqst0ovzndj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    cfg = json.load(f)\n\n# Fix tts dmPolicy back to allowlist (inherit from global)\ntts = cfg['channels']['feishu']['accounts']['tts']\ntts['dmPolicy'] = 'allowlist'\n\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(cfg, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)\n\nprint('Fixed tts dmPolicy=allowlist')\nprint('tts account:', json.dumps(tts, indent=2))\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2226,"output":674,"cacheRead":81952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84852,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779544599200,"responseId":"0660e51744e2ea9e92443bba3d803608"}}
{"type":"message","id":"16b09b0b","parentId":"b6c62342","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:56:51.733Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gjqst0ovzndj_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed tts dmPolicy=allowlist\ntts account: {\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"appId\": \"cli_a930f78f51399bc6\",\n  \"appSecret\": \"sWYftq…ThbY\",\n  \"connectionMode\": \"websocket\",\n  \"dmPolicy\": \"allowlist\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":61,"aggregated":"Fixed tts dmPolicy=allowlist\ntts account: {\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"appId\": \"cli_a930f78f51399bc6\",\n  \"appSecret\": \"***\",\n  \"connectionMode\": \"websocket\",\n  \"dmPolicy\": \"allowlist\"\n}","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779544611731}}
{"type":"message","id":"9eb23255","parentId":"16b09b0b","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:56:56.536Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, I set tts dmPolicy back to allowlist. Now let me trigger a gateway restart.\n","thinkingSignature":"30c8aa970a18a98742022e4a6d3757a9f56fe9b8070dba0616a3181469b623f3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4cuzsn9itng7_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"restart","note":"tts dmPolicy 改回 allowlist，继承全局白名单，重启生效","reason":"tts dmPolicy 改回 allowlist，与其他 bot 一致"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":270,"output":95,"cacheRead":84160,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84525,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779544611997,"responseId":"0660e5241b7c6aeb58a8db8a1cb46b2f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"32b2c872","parentId":"9eb23255","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:56:56.728Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4cuzsn9itng7_1","toolName":"gateway","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"pid\": 523018,\n  \"signal\": \"SIGUSR1\",\n  \"delayMs\": 0,\n  \"reason\": \"tts dmPolicy 改回 allowlist，与其他 bot 一致\",\n  \"mode\": \"emit\",\n  \"coalesced\": true,\n  \"cooldownMsApplied\": 0\n}"}],"details":{"ok":true,"pid":523018,"signal":"SIGUSR1","delayMs":0,"reason":"tts dmPolicy 改回 allowlist，与其他 bot 一致","mode":"emit","coalesced":true,"cooldownMsApplied":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779544616726}}
{"type":"message","id":"f1e7f15e","parentId":"32b2c872","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:57:04.655Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so I changed tts dmPolicy to \"allowlist\" which will inherit the global allowFrom=['ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb']. This is the same pattern as all other bots (they inherit the global allowlist with the user's open_id).\n\nBut there's still a critical issue: the user's messages to TK bot are NOT going to feishu[tts]. They're going to feishu[kiit]. This is a routing problem that dmPolicy won't fix.\n\nThe real question is: why are messages from ou_f590c429 going to kiit instead of tts?\n\nWait - I just realized something. \n\nWhen a user sends a message to TK bot, Feishu routes it to the TK app's WebSocket connection, which should be feishu[tts]. But the journal shows messages from ou_f590c429 reaching feishu[kiit] instead. This could mean either the user is actually messaging kiit not TK bot, the TK app's WebSocket connection is broken, or there's a Feishu routing issue. The user's confirmation that they're messaging TK bot makes this particularly strange.\n\nI'm wondering if the problem is on Feishu's end—when the app's WebSocket connection drops, Feishu might queue messages temporarily, but if the reconnection fails repeatedly, messages could get routed to the default app instead. Or maybe the user is inadvertently messaging kiit because both bots appear in Feishu's search results and it's unclear which one they're selecting.\n\nLet me reconsider the architecture: the user sends to TK bot specifically, Feishu routes to the cli_a930f78f51399bc6 WebSocket connection, feishu[tts] receives and checks the allowFrom list, then the binding routes to the tts agent. So I need to verify whether feishu[tts] is actually receiving messages at all—I'll look for any feishu[tts] messages from ou_f590c429 in the logs.\n\nThe user's statement \"只有 选品大师没有回复\" is key—TK bot doesn't reply but kiit does, so feishu[kiit] is receiving messages while feishu[tts] isn't. This means TK bot's app isn't getting its messages routed properly. But other bots work, so there's something specific about TK bot's Feishu app configuration or connection that's broken.\n\nI'm thinking through the sequence: when the user sends to TK bot (appId cli_a930f78f51399bc6), Feishu should route to that app's WebSocket. The fact that messages are going to kiit instead suggests either the user is actually messaging kiit despite thinking they're messaging TK bot, or the TK app's connection isn't properly registered with Feishu's message routing system. The connection might be established but not correctly configured for message delivery.\n","thinkingSignature":"51863eafeb2168d44437ecd2c7044c5312c6ec3624348eebf653124f63c3eb7f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9lxrx8mv29cu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sleep 8 && journalctl -n 200 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"22:0|21:5[89]\" | grep -iE \"feishu\\[tts\\]|feishu\\[kiit\\]\" | head -30","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":178,"output":678,"cacheRead":84416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85272,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779544616983,"responseId":"0660e5298e9c6cc09cb581fc4b76f454"}}
