{"type":"message","id":"bb388881","parentId":"0e42d692","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:57:33.862Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see something very important! \n\nIn the recent logs:\n```\n21:57:09 [feishu] feishu[tts]: sender ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 not in DM allowlist → (old dmPolicy=pairing)\n21:57:09 [feishu] feishu[tts]: dispatching to agent (session=agent:tts:main)  → (after dmPolicy changed to allowlist!)\n```\n\nWait, the first message at 21:57:09 - the sender was `ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` and it was \"not in DM allowlist\" but then STILL dispatched? That seems inconsistent.\n\n\nActually, let me trace this more carefully. The sender is `ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68`, which was rejected with \"not in DM allowlist\" at 21:57:09 when dmPolicy was still pairing, but then at 21:57:16 there's a message from that same sender that gets registered to the session and dispatches successfully.\n\nSo the dmPolicy must have switched to allowlist by 21:57:09, allowing `ou_f590c429` through. But `ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` was still paired with agent `tts`, which means it's not in the tts allowFrom list yet it still dispatched. That's odd.\n\nActually, I think I'm confusing the messages here. The 21:57:09 message was rejected, but then at 21:57:16 a different sender (`ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb`) got a pairing request created when dmPolicy was set to pairing mode. So it seems like the system was allowing `ou_f590c429` through even in pairing mode because it was creating a pairing request, but `ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` was already paired and bypassed the allowFrom check entirely. Now I need to check what happened around 22:00.\n","thinkingSignature":"712565cba02ae3d6160ee8736a8b53318318953f4b53f0912e087f9a4c540809"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pppw62gnm5fx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl -n 200 --no-pager 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"22:0[0-9]\