{"type":"message","id":"a91f689f","parentId":"017a4471","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:58:16.810Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The main/kiit session (405b68a9) is still long-running and currently doing a tool_call (exec). This means the kiit main session is busy running a tool call right now. It might be the feishu_im_user_message tool call that triggered the auth flow!\n\nSo the kiit session is stuck on a tool call. The tool it's running might be the feishu_im_user_message send that triggered the auth card. Let me check what tool it's actually running.\n\nActually, the session is running `exec` as the active tool. This could be the feishu auth flow triggering something.\n\nBut more importantly - the tts session IS working now! The dmPolicy=allowlist fix worked for tts (at least for ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68).\n\n\nNow I need to see if ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb is actually routing to tts when it sends a message to the TK bot. The channel reload is still deferred, which might be preventing the new config from fully applying, but ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 did route successfully. Let me check the current tts sessions to see if the user's messages are hitting tts now.","thinkingSignature":"1acfe6505c68ceabdfc2b2838aa273a1ddcf3031809f5072d77d9354d0d5da32"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tklqq64b9bmc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/sessions/sessions.json') as f:\n    data = json.load(f)\nimport datetime\nprint('tts sessions now:')\nfor k, v in data.items():\n    ts = v.get('updatedAt', 0)\n    age_min = (datetime.datetime.now().timestamp() * 1000 - ts) / 60000\n    print(f'  {k}')\n    print(f'    age: {age_min:.1f} min ago')\n    print(f'    origin accountId: {v.get(\\\"origin\\\",{}).get(\\\"accountId\\\")}')\n    print()\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","u