{"type":"message","id":"d5993e04","parentId":"92c52290","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:58:37.125Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good news! I can see:\n\n1. `feishu[tts]: dispatching to agent (session=agent:tts:main)` at 21:57:46\n2. `feishu[tts]: dispatch complete (queuedFinal=true, replies=1)` at 21:58:07\n\nSo tts IS dispatching messages and getting replies! The tts agent is processing messages from `ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` and dispatch complete with 1 reply.\n\nBut the key question: did tts receive a message from `ou_f590c429` (HALEI)? I need to check if there's a session for HALEI's user open_id under tts.\n\n\nNow checking the sessions.json, I notice `agent:tts:main` is only 0.2 minutes old (just updated), but there's no `agent:tts:feishu:direct:ou_f590c429` session. The feishu direct session with HALEI's open_id hasn't been created yet, which means tts hasn't received any messages from that user.\n\nLooking back at what actually happened: ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 has an old feishu session (36076.6 minutes ago), but the tts agent is currently routing messages from that user to `agent:tts:main` instead of creating a new feishu direct session. So the routing mechanism for that user is going to the main session rather than establishing a fresh feishu session.\n\nThe core issue is that my user `ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb` doesn't have a feishu direct session with tts at all—only `ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` does. That's why the messages aren't being routed to the right place.\n\nActually, I need to reconsider what's happening here. The `ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68` messages were from the test user, not from me. My actual messages are still not creating a tts feishu direct session, which means something is still broken in the routing.\n\nWait, let me think about this from first principles again. When someone sends a DM to the TK bot, it should route to feishu[tts], and if the sender is in allowlist, it dispatches to the agent with a new feishu direct session. But I'm not getting that session creation for my user ID.\n\nActually, I should check if maybe my messages are going to a different place entirely. Let me look at the 22:00 timeframe logs to see what's actually happening with feishu[tts]. Looking at the dispatch logs more carefully - tts got a message at 21:57:30 and completed dispatch at 21:57:30, then received another message at 21:57:30 and dispatched again at 21:57:30. So tts has received multiple messages from that test user and is processing them normally.\n\nBut I haven't seen a single feishu[tts] log entry for my user ID yet. That's the real issue - my messages are still going to kiit instead of tts. So fixing the dmPolicy didn't solve the routing problem. I need to dig into the gateway code to understand why messages to the tk bot are being routed to kiit instead.\n","thinkingSignature":"c71fe409375641aa351addb203b88381c76d6031130f99b4e1c51257ded18696"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_23lmab530ywv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"accountId.*tts\\|tts.*accountId\\|kiit.*accountId\\|accountId.*kiit\" /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/gateway.js 2>/dev/null | head -5","timeout":5}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_23lmab530ywv_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"defaultAccount\\|route.*accountId\\|dispatching.*agent\\|dispatch.*accountId\" /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/feishu/index.js 2>/dev/null | head -10","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":524,"output":910,"cacheRead":90016,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91450,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779544708603,"responseId":"0660e58526e8f0ca611d1d7281ac3ab4"}}
