{"type":"message","id":"60d3095d","parentId":"2ac93a77","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:58:51.357Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user confirmed it works! The message came through Feishu[default] with a message from `ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb`. This confirms KIIT (main agent) is now responding.\n\nBut wait - the question was about TK 选品大师 (tts), not KIIT. Let me check if the user is saying TK works now, or KIIT works now.\n\nThe user said \"可以了\" (it works now). Given the context of the conversation - we were troubleshooting TK 选品大师 not responding. The system message shows Feishu[default] DM, which is KIIT.\n\n\nI'm getting confused about which bot actually started working. The system message shows KIIT responding, but the user might be confirming KIIT works while TK still has issues. Let me look back at what was actually broken - TK wasn't responding to messages, while KIIT was supposed to be working but wasn't replying either. 看起来 TK 选品大师现在能正常处理消息了，dispatch complete 和 replies=1 的日志证实了这一点。不过还有一个关键问题悬而未决：为什么用户发给 TK 的消息没有路由到对应的 tts 账号，尽管飞书的消息路由机制应该是基于 bot 的 open_id 来处理的。 Kiit is working now with the allowlist policy and your open_id in the allowlist, but I'm realizing there's a routing mismatch — your Feishu[default] messages show accountId=\"default\" while the config shows defaultAccount=\"kiit\", and there's no binding for default. Either the binding system works differently than I thought, or Feishu routes differently when there's no explicit route. But the key issue is whether TK can now receive messages directly from you through its feishu[tts] connection, since I still haven't seen that happen.\n","thinkingSignature":"eb10d1e76a47c36c734649bce923acd5836342f9383aedfb677e605e96f87fff"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n太好了！🎉 TK 选品大师现在能回复了！\n\n不过让我确认一下——你现在是在 **TK 选品大师** 的窗口发消息收到回复，还是在 **KIIT** 窗口收到的回复？\n\n因为之前的问题是 TK bot 不响应，KIIT 窗口是正常的。如果现在 TK 也修好了，那是哪个在回复？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"M